(5763, 883, 'Grill eggplant while sauce cooks.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5764, 883, 'Heat grill pan over high heat until hot. Peel skin from eggplant and discard.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5765, 883, 'Cut eggplant long-ways into 8 (1/3-inch-thick) slices. Lightly rush both sides of slices with 2 teaspoons oil (total), then season with salt and pepper. Grill slices in batches, turning over once l, until golden brown and tender, about 4 minutes, then transfer to a tray.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5766, 883, 'Stir together ricotta and 1/2 cup Parmesan, basil, pepper, and remaining salt. Divide cheese mixture among slices.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5767, 883, 'Roll up each slice.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5768, 883, 'Place rolls in a small casserole dish and bake until cheese starts to melt, about 10 minutes.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5769, 883, 'Meanwhile, cook linguine to package directions.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5770, 883, 'Serve rolls over linguine, topped with sauce and sprinkled with 1 tablespoon Parmesan each.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5771, 884, 'Preheat the oven to 375F. Slice the zucchini lengthwise and lay it flat on a cookie sheet.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5772, 884, 'Bake in the oven for 15 minutes. This is very important in order to bake out most of the liquid.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5773, 884, 'In a medium saucepan, saut the onion and bell pepper.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5774, 884, 'Add in the ground turkey and cook thoroughly.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5775, 884, 'Mix in the tomato sauce and seasonings. Turn the heat to low and allow it to simmer for 5 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5776, 884, 'In a separate bowl, mix together the ingredients for your cheese mixture and set aside. In a 9 x 13 baking dish, layer the bottom with zucchini noodles.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5777, 884, 'Spread the cheese mixture over the zucchini and add a layer of meat sauce. Repeat these steps to create the layers for your zucchini lasagna. Top with mozzarella cheese and cover the baking dish with foil.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5778, 884, 'Bake the zucchini lasagna in the oven for 30 minutes.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5779, 884, 'Remove the foil and then cook an additional 10 minutes.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5780, 884, 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 5 minutes before serving.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5781, 885, 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Slice French loaf into 1/2-inch-thick slices, and brush (or spray, if you have one of those nifty Misto things) with olive oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5782, 885, 'Place slices on baking sheet and toast in oven for 10-15 minutes, or until edges are a deep golden brown.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5783, 885, 'Remove from oven and set aside.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5784, 885, 'While those are in the oven, make your pesto. In a food processor, combine basil leaves, garlic clove, pine nuts and Romano cheese. Pulse until pesto is coarse in texture, like coarse sand.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5785, 885, 'Add in olive oil and process until fully incorporated. Taste.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5786, 885, 'Add salt and pepper, if needed. Scrape pesto into a serving bowl or dish and set aside. (You should have about 3/4 cup.)', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5787, 886, 'Heat oil in saut pan.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5788, 886, 'Add chopped shallots. Saut until translucent.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5789, 886, 'Add crab meat, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Saut until warmed through. Take off heat and cool.Once filling is cooled add ricotta.Separate out the lasagna sheets or wonton wrappers.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5790, 886, 'Place about 1 tbls of filling on center of sheet (you don\'t want too much or filing will come out when cooking).', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5791, 886, 'Place dollops of filling about 2-3 inches apart.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5792, 886, 'Brush egg white around the filling.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5793, 886, 'Place another sheet on top of the sheet with filling.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5794, 886, 'Cut out rounds with a cookie cutter (or a glass - whatever works).With a fork, press the sides of rounds together to prevent them from separating during cooking.Bring pot of water to a boil.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5795, 886, 'Add finished ravioli to pot of boiling water. Cook about 6 minutes, or until done.After they are done place on paper towel to absorb water.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5796, 887, 'Pound the beef between two sheets of plastic wrap with a meat tenderizer mallet until about  to  inch thick being careful to prevent holes or tears in the meat. Any holes that do happen can be patched with a piece of prosciutto or salami during the next step.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5797, 887, 'Place the prosciutto and salami in a single layer over the beef. If there are any holes or thin places in the beef, make sure to place the meat over those areas.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5798, 887, 'Spread the breadcrumbs over the salami in an even layer leaving an inch on all sides to make rolling the meat easier.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5799, 887, 'Sprinkle the cheese over the breadcrumbs and drizzle 2 tablespoons of the olive oil over all.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5800, 887, 'Carefully fold the edges over and begin to roll the beef.  Tie the roll in several places with kitchen twine and gently rub the outside of the roll with the remaining oil.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5801, 887, 'Heat a non-stick skillet over medium high heat. With the aid of tongs, sear the roll all over, including the ends, until nicely browned all over. While the meat is browning, heat the marinara sauce, garlic and wine in a Dutch oven or pan large enough to hold the size of the roll.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5802, 887, 'Place the browned braciole in the sauce and bring to a gentle simmer.  Cover and braise, over low heat until tender. The braciole in the photograph took 3 hours until a fork inserted into the meat slid in easily.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5803, 887, 'When tender, carefully remove the beef roll from the sauce and set on a platter.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5804, 887, 'Let the roll cool for about 5-10 minutes and remove the string. Slice the braciole and serve with pasta or gnocchi with the sauce over the top and plenty of parmesan cheese.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5805, 888, 'In a large stock pan over medium-high heat, add the olive oil and the onion. Allow the onion to cook until it is tender (about 3 minutes).', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5806, 888, 'Add the tomato (or marinara sauce) and garlic and incorporate it into the mixture. Cook for just 1-2 minutes (be careful not to burn the garlic).', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5807, 888, 'Add the vegetable stock, water, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Bring this to a boil and then add your pasta. Lower the heat and allow the pasta to cook until its about 3/4 of the way finished (still slightly firm).', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5808, 888, 'Add your beans and allow the mixture to continue cooking until the pasta is fully cooked (about 10-15 minutes).', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5809, 888, 'Add the parsley toward the end of your cooking time. Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5810, 888, 'Serve in individual bowls with extra parsley as garnish and sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5811, 889, 'Make the dough.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5812, 889, 'Mix the yeast with the water and honey in a large bowl.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5813, 889, 'Let sit for 5-10 minutes until the yeast mixture becomes fluffy. Then add 1 cups of flour to the yeast mixture and mix together.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5814, 889, 'Then slowly add 1 more cup of flour to the mixture.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5815, 889, 'Combine till a dough is formed. Turn out dough onto a floured surface. Knead the dough with the heel of your hand, then pull forward and repeat. Continue, while slowly adding the last  cup of of flour to the dough. Kneading should take about 5 minutes and dough should be very slightly sticky. Make sure not to over knead.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5816, 889, 'Place dough in a large greased bowl and cover with plastic wrap.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5817, 889, 'Place bowl in a place with no drafts, such as the microwave or a cold oven.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5818, 889, 'Let sit until dough rises in size, about 3-4 hours.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5819, 889, 'Once ready to make pizza, preheat oven to 450 degrees Fahrenheit. On a large rimmed baking sheet, sprinkle cornmeal evenly over the bottom of the pan.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5820, 889, 'Place dough on baking sheet and with fingers gently spread the dough to the size of the pan.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5821, 889, 'Using a spoon, spread the pasta sauce evenly over the dough, leaving a wide berth around the edges.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5822, 889, 'Add dollops of pesto to the pizza.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5823, 889, 'Sprinkle mozzarella and cheddar cheese over the pizza. Evenly place bell pepper, red onion and olives on pizza.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5824, 889, 'Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over the top.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5825, 889, 'Place in oven and cook for 15 minutes, rotating  way through. Crust should be golden brown and cheese should be bubbling.', 15, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5826, 889, 'Top the pizza with fresh tomatoes.', 16, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5827, 889, 'Serve and enjoy.', 17, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5828, 890, 'Put the eggplant on a baking sheet and brush with olive oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5829, 890, 'Place under the broiler until soft.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5830, 890, 'Remove and allow to cool.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5831, 890, 'Meanwhile, heat the sauce in a small saucepan.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5832, 890, 'Heat the remaining oil and cook the onion for 5 minutes. Then add the garlic and cook for an additional minute.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5833, 890, 'Add the onion and garlic to the sauce.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5834, 890, 'Arrange the eggplant across the bottom of a 8 x 6 baking dish and then scatter cheese on top. Repeat layers until you run out of eggplant. Finish off with sauce, basil and remaining cheese.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5835, 890, 'Bake for 40 minutes and 37', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5836, 890, 'Optional: If you prefer you can fry the eggplant in a bit of olive oil. Then, soak up oil on a paper towel.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5837, 891, 'Prepare shells according to package directions minus 2 minutes (the shells will finish in the sauce) and drain.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5838, 891, 'Lay the shells out on foil or a backing sheet so that they don\'t stick together. Discard any that are broken.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5839, 891, 'Meanwhile, in a sautee pan over medium-high heat, brown the sausage.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5840, 891, 'Drain any excess fat and add the onion. Continue to cook until the onions are translucent.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5841, 891, 'Add garlic and cook for an additional minute.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5842, 891, 'Add water, stewed tomatoes and tomato paste. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5843, 891, 'In a large bowl, combine ricotta, 1/2 cup mozzarella, 1/2 cup Parmesan, basil and egg whites.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5844, 891, 'Preheat oven to 350F.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5845, 891, 'Spay a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with non stick. Fill shells with about 1 tablespoon of the cheese mixture each and place in a tight single layer in the baking dish.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5846, 891, 'Pour the ragu over the shells and top with remaining mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Cover and bake until the sauce is bubbling, about 30 minutes.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5847, 891, 'Remove, uncover and let stand about 10 minutes.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5848, 892, 'Cut the pumpkin, clean out the innards and place cut face down in a baking dish with a 1/4 inch of water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5849, 892, 'Bake in a 400 degree oven for 45 minutes until the insides are soft and cooked.Scoop out the cooked flesh and puree with the tiniest bit of milk to make a smooth puree.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5850, 892, 'Saute the onions and garlic in butter until translucent.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5851, 892, 'Add in the barley and toast for a couple of minutes.Season with salt, pepper, cumin, thyme and oregano.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5852, 892, 'Add two cups of stock and cook until the liquid is almost absorbed.Stir in the pumpkin puree.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5853, 892, 'Add the rest of the stock in half cup measures and stirring until it is fully absorbed.Slowly, the barley will become creamy as the starch releases.When you are done with all the stock, remove from heat and stir in the sour cream.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5854, 892, 'Serve immediately garnished with mint leaves and a drop of pumkiny-sour cream.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5855, 893, 'Boil pasta as directed.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5856, 893, 'Drain pasta, reserving 1/2 cup pasta cooking water.Return pasta and reserved cooking water to pot.Slice green onions.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5857, 893, 'Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a skillet on medium-high until hot.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5858, 893, 'Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5859, 893, 'Add chicken to skillet and cook 7 minutes or until chicken is cooked through, stirring occasionally.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5860, 893, 'Transfer chicken to medium bowl; set aside.To same skillet, add remaining 2 teaspoons oil; reduce heat to medium.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5861, 893, 'Add green onions and garlic and cook 1 minute, stirring.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5862, 893, 'Add asparagus and red pepper; cook 6 to 7 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.Stir in cream, crushed red pepper, and 1/4 teaspoon salt.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5863, 893, 'Heat mixture to boiling on medium high.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5864, 893, 'Add halved tomatoes, lemon zest and lemon juice.Cook 1-2 minutes on medium heat, until tomatoes just start to break down.Stir in reserved chicken pieces and remove skillet from heat.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5865, 893, 'Add Parmesan, chicken mixture, and basil to pot with pasta and reserved cooking water. Stir to combine.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5866, 893, 'Garnish with more basil and Parmesan, if you\'re so inclined.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5867, 894, 'Preheat oven to 400', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5868, 894, 'Place water and yeast in a mixing bowl and let stand for 5-10 minutes or until frothy.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5869, 894, 'Add olive oil to the water yeast combo.Shift together salt, sugar and flour in a separate bowl.Using a dough hook attachment, add dry mixture to wet in  cup increments until the dough comes together to form a slightly tacky ball.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5870, 894, 'Remove dough from mixer and lightly knead.Leave to rest covered by a clean tea towel for ten minutes.Divide dough in two and stretch one half to fit an 11-inch pizza pan.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5871, 894, 'Place other half in the fridge for another time or form into a second pizza.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5872, 894, 'Spread pizza sauce over the dough and sprinkle with chili pepper flakes and  the red onion.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5873, 894, 'Sprinkle with cheese and arrange the salami so it is evenly distributed over the entire pizza.Top with remaining red onion, red pepper and basil leaves.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5874, 894, 'Place in the oven and bake for 12-15 minutes rotating halfway through.When golden and bubbling, remove from the oven and let stand for ten minutes before slicing.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5875, 894, 'Serve with a sprinkling of fresh ground pepper and a nice cold beer.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5876, 895, 'In a food processor or blender, combine the pumpkin, applesauce, banana and nut butter until smooth.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5877, 895, 'Add protein powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie or apple pie spice, vanilla, and brown sugar.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5878, 895, 'Place the oats in a large bowl and add the creamed mixture.  Stir, folding in the pumpkin seeds (optional).', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5879, 895, 'Bake at 350 for 30-40 minutes.  Mine took roughly 32 minutes to be baked.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5880, 896, 'In a large sauce pan, heat oil over medium-high heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5881, 896, 'Add sausage, crumble and brown.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5882, 896, 'Add onion and garlic and saute until onions are just tender, about three minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5883, 896, 'Meanwhile, create a bouquet garni in cheese cloth with the basil, oregano and fennel.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5884, 896, 'Add it and all remaining ingredients except the kale and buttermilk, bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes are cooked, 10-15 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5885, 896, 'Add kale and simmer until it is just tender, less than 5 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5886, 896, 'Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5887, 896, 'Add pepper to taste, you shouldn\'t need salt. Top with about a tablespoon of cheese.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5888, 896, 'Serve with a warm, crusty bread.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5889, 897, 'Heat iron skillet on medium-high heat and cook elk Italian sausage until brown.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5890, 897, 'Remove from heat and set aside.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5891, 897, 'Add 3 tablespoons of grape seed oil to the skillet. Saut minced garlic cloves and diced shallot in pan until they begin to soften and brown.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5892, 897, 'Add sliced  onion, sliced mushrooms and fresh oregano leaves to garlic and shallot mixture. Stir and continue to saut until onions become translucent and soft. Generally about 10-12 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5893, 897, 'Remove from heat when ready.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5894, 897, 'Heat oven to 400 degrees.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5895, 897, 'I like to take the left over oil from the pan and brush the top and bottom of my pizza crust.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(5896, 897, 'Place pizza crust upside down on cookie sheet and place in oven for about 5-6 minutes or until the top of the pizza crust begins to brown.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5897, 897, 'Remove from oven.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5898, 897, 'Turn pizza crust right side up and cover the top of the crust with the ricotta cheese.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5899, 897, 'Add tomato sauce, top with elk Italian sausage, and add mushroom and onion mixture and then top off with chopped basil and fresh grated parmesan cheese.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5900, 897, 'Place in oven and bake approximately 12-14 minutes or until cheese is melted.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5901, 897, 'Remove from oven and enjoy.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5902, 898, 'Depending on how think your chicken breasts are, place them under plastic wrap and pound until thin. If you don\'t have a meat pounder, use a heavy pot of skillet. You can also fillet these with a knife.Get 3 pie plates or containers. Put flour in one, beaten eggs in one and bread crumbs in one.Dredge chicken breast in flour, then in the egg wash, and then the bread crumbs.Fry cutlets in vegetable oil over med heat. Fry until golden brown.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5903, 898, 'Spread a little marinara on the bottom of a 13x9 baking dish.Make a layer of chicken.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5904, 898, 'Add more marinara. Use most of the first quart.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5905, 898, 'Add a layer of the cheeses. Repeat layers.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5906, 898, 'Sprinkle parsley over last layer of cheese.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5907, 898, 'Bake in a pre-heated 350 degree oven covered for 35 minutes. uncover and bake until top is bubbly!', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5908, 899, 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5909, 899, 'Cut the bread into  inch cubes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5910, 899, 'Place them on a baking sheet.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5911, 899, 'Toss with 2 tablespoons of olive oil and then generously sprinkle with Italian herb seasoning. (I use McCormick spice grinder.)', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5912, 899, 'Toss bread cubes for 15 minutes, flipping halfway through.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5913, 899, 'Place toasted bread, tomatoes, cucumber, and mozzarella in a salad bowl.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5914, 899, 'Drizzle with vinaigrette.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5915, 899, 'Sprinkle with fresh basil.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5916, 899, 'In a bowl combine garlic, mustard, and vinegar. Using an emulsion blender slowly add in olive oil. Blend until emulsion is created.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5917, 899, 'Add salt and pepper to season.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5918, 900, 'Put the cold precooked polenta in a mixer and blend it with the egg until creamy.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5919, 900, 'Add the buckwheat flour. You will need more or less 1/3 of a cup, but a lot depends on how sticky your polenta.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5920, 900, 'Add enough flour to get a soft dough that doesn\'t stick to your hand.Form the gnocchi on a floured surface by rolling out the dough in long logs, more or less as thick as a thumb and then cut them in gnocchi. If you want the gnocchi to look super nice, roll them on a fork to give them the characteristic stripes (I never do).', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5921, 900, 'Place the gnocchi in the fridge while you prepare the sauce.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5922, 900, 'Cut the savoy cabbage in stripes, wash it and stew it with a bit of water until wilted.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5923, 900, 'Drain it and sautee it with 1 spoon butter and salt until cooked.Prepare the cheese by dicing it and the rest of the butter by melting it with the sage and the garlic.Cook the gnocchi in salted boiling water in batches. Throw 10-20 gnocchi in the pot of boiling water and fish them out once they start floating.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5924, 900, 'Drain them and add them to a bowl. Dress with cheese, cabbage and butter and keep layering the ingredients in the bowl until you run out.Do not mix the gnocchi in the bowl, as they are rather soft and would break. If the cheese didn\'t melt much, you can microwave the bowl for a couple of minutes.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5925, 900, 'Serve piping hot.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5926, 901, 'Take a large soup pot, heat to medium and add olive oil and bacon drippings', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5927, 901, 'Add all above veggies and herbs, except tomatoes and white beans', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5928, 901, 'Cook and stir until chard and cabbage begins to wilt, about 5-10 minutes', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5929, 901, 'Cover and cook until veggies ar tender, about 10 minutes', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5930, 901, 'Add drained tomatoes', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5931, 901, 'Turn up the heat to medium-high and cook for another 3-5 minutes, stirring', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5932, 901, 'Stir in chicken stock, white beans, salt and parmesean rind', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5933, 901, 'Bring to a boil, then simmer partially covered for about 30 minutes', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5934, 901, 'Remove parmesean rind', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5935, 901, 'Stir in Orzo', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5936, 901, 'Continue to simmer for 15 minutes', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5937, 901, 'Taste!', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5938, 901, 'Drizzle each serving with extra virgin olive oil', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5939, 901, 'Add cracked black pepper if desired', 14, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5940, 902, 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until the oil is shimmering.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5941, 902, 'Add onion and 1/2 t. salt, cook until onion is softened and beginning to brown, about 5-7 minutes. Stir in garlic, tomato paste, oregano and red pepper flakes. Cook, stirring constantly until garlic is fragrant and the tomato paste is distributed., about a minute.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5942, 902, 'Add ground beef, cook until the meat is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5943, 902, 'Pour the diced tomatoes (undrained) into a large measuring cup, add enough water to the tomatoes to measure 4 cups.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5944, 902, 'When the meat is browned, scatter the lasagna noodles evenly over the top of the meat (do not stir).', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5945, 902, 'Pour the diced tomatoes and water, and the tomato sauce evenly over the top of the noodles. Cover and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring once or twice during cook time, until pasta is tender, about 20 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5946, 902, 'Remove skillet from heat, stir in the 1/2 c. Parmesan. Season to taste with salt & pepper. Dollop rounded tablespoons of the ricotta evenly over the top, cover and let stand for 5 minutes, to let the ricotta warm through.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5947, 902, 'Sprinkle with the basil and remaining 2 T. Parmesan.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5948, 903, 'Peel eggplant.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5949, 903, 'Place the eggplant upright on the cutting board and slice the eggplant in long thin vertical slices.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5950, 903, 'Sprinkle some salt and black pepper on eggplant.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5951, 903, 'Heat one tbsp of olive oil in a pan and fry the eggplant slices lightly from both sides. Keep aside.Now heat rest of 1 tbsp of olive oil and put onions in it. Stir-fry until translucent.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5952, 903, 'Add some garlic salt, red crushed pepper, and Italian seasoning, and mix well. Take onions off heat.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5953, 903, 'Heat the marinara sauce in a pan and adjust the spices per your taste. Now layer the baking dish with 1 cup of sauce in the bottom.Now taking one strip of pasta at a time, start layering it with 2 slices of eggplant, then onions and top it off with some cheese. Start rolling pasta starting from one end and go till end. Put it seam side down in the baking dish. Repeat this process until all the pasta sheets are finished.Cover the pasta completely with the rest of the sauce.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5954, 903, 'Sprinkle rest 1 cup of the cheese on top of it.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5955, 903, 'Bake at 400 degree F in a pre-heated oven for about 25 minutes.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5956, 903, 'Let cool down for 5-7 min and serve warm with ur favorite pasta or soup.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5957, 904, 'Start by prepping your pancetta and vegetables.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5958, 904, 'Cut the pancetta into medium sized chunks (larger than bite sized, because they\'ll cook down in the pan) and roughly chop some carrots and celery. Then peel and chop a large russet potato. I keep these chunks larger, because they break down a lot in the soup.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5959, 904, 'Next, dice some yellow onion and mince some garlic.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5960, 904, 'Throw the olive oil in a large stock (or soup) pot and let it warm up over medium heat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5961, 904, 'Once warm, add in the pancetta and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally, until lightly browned.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5962, 904, 'Then, add the onions, carrots, celery, and potato to the pot and cook for medium heat for 8 minutes, or until the vegetables begin to soften. Again, stir occasionally. In the last 30 - 60 seconds, add in the garlic, dried thyme, dried basil, and red pepper flakes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5963, 904, 'Now add in the canned tomatoes, chicken broth, and a bay leaf. Give it a quick stir and season with salt and pepper. Don\'t season too aggressively, because the pancetta and chicken broth already have salt. You can add more later on, if necessary!', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5964, 904, 'Bring the soup to a boil over high heat. Once boiling, lower to medium and simmer uncovered for 10-12 minutes.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5965, 904, 'Then add in the dry quinoa and cook for another 15 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and the quinoa is cooked.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5966, 904, 'Now discard the bay leaf and add in the beans, white wine, and pesto.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5967, 904, 'Remove the soup from the heat and stir in the baby spinach.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5968, 904, 'Re-season with salt and pepper and place back on the stove to warm it back up, if necessary!', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5969, 904, 'Serve immediately with an optional sprinkle of shredded parmesan cheese and a side of crusty baguette smothered in pesto!', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5970, 905, 'Prepare the eggplant: Peel the eggplant and cut lengthwise into long slices, about 1/4 of an inch thick.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5971, 905, 'Layer the slices in a colander.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5972, 906, 'Preheat the oven to 425F.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5973, 906, 'Heat butter and olive oil in a saucepan and saute the onion, garlic, celery, carrots and herbs until lightly golden.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5974, 906, 'Add the vin santo or Marsala and bring to a boil. Boil for about 2 minutes, then remove from heat.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5975, 906, 'Place the meats, salt and pepper in a large bowl and mix together, then add the vegetables. Squeeze the bread of excess milk and break it into the mixture.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5976, 906, 'Add the 2 raw eggs. Using your hands, combine mixture well.Line a large rectangular terrine, casserole, or loaf pan (about 14 inches long) with foil and brush with oil.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5977, 906, 'Place half of the meat mixture in the pan and press down evenly. Arrange the hard boiled eggs in a line down the center, then cover with the remaining meat mixture. Press the mixture down well.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5978, 906, 'Bake the loaf on the bottom shelf of the oven for about 50 minutes; it should be lightly browned on top. Turn onto a serving dish. It is delicious served hot or cold.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5979, 907, 'Cut up the cauliflower and blend (just the florets, not the stems) until the cauliflower is a rice-like consistency.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5980, 907, 'Remove the cauliflower from the blender and place in a cloth.Squeeze out as much water as possible until the cauliflower is as dry as possible.Then, in a bowl, place the cauliflower, egg, flour, salt, pepper, mixed herbs and garlic powder.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5981, 907, 'Mix all the ingredients well.Grease up some parchment paper and place on a tray.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5982, 907, 'Place the cauliflower on the tray and use your hands to flatten into your desired shape, making the edges thicker to form the \'crust\'.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5983, 907, 'Place in the oven for approximately ten minutes or until browned and hardened like a pizza base.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5984, 907, 'Remove from the oven and top with the tomato puree, mozzarella, sliced tomatoes, fresh herbs and pepperoni before placing back in the oven and baking for a further ten minutes or until the cheese has nicely melted.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5985, 908, 'Peel the eggplants, slice them (about 1 cm thick) and season with salt. Set aside for about 20 minutes.Rinse eggplant slices and wipe with a paper towel to absorb all the water.Prepare two bowls, one with beaten eggs (with a pinch of salt) and one with breadcrumbs mixed with Parmesan (2 tablespoons)Dip sliced eggplant in beaten eggs, then the bread crumb mixture and coat thoroughly.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5986, 908, 'Place eggplant on baking sheet.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5987, 908, 'Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes or until golden brown.Marinara Sauce: In a saucepan put 3 tablespoons of olive oil and a clove of crushed garlic. Fry it then add tomato puree, season with salt, pepper and oregano to taste and let simmer about 5-10 minutes.At the end add the chopped parsley.Top each eggplant piece with two tablespoons marinara sauce and one tablespoon mozzarella cheese. Return to oven and bake for 8-10 minutes additional year or until cheese is melted.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5988, 908, 'Serve!', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5989, 909, 'Bring a large pot of water to boil. When the water is boiling, add 1 T of salt along with the pasta to the pot. Stir well. Cook according to package directions or for about 6-7 minutes for fresh pasta (until al dente).', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5990, 909, 'Put the butter and cream in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently, until the cream has reduced almost by half.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5991, 909, 'Add the nutmeg, lemon zest, black pepper, and salt, to taste. Stir to combine and set aside.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5992, 909, 'When pasta is finished cooking, drain and add to the sauce in the skillet.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5993, 909, 'Add cheese and toss to coat pasta in sauce and cheese. Check seasonings and add more salt and pepper as needed.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5994, 909, 'Serve immediately.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5995, 910, 'In a large skillet heat up oil, add garlic and onions; saut for 3 minutes  then add mushrooms and continue for further 5 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5996, 910, 'Add bay leaves.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5997, 910, 'Stir in rice.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5998, 910, 'Add vegetable or chicken stock, one ladle at a time. Simmer until liquid has been absorbed; dont forget to stir to avoid sticking.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(5999, 910, 'Continue to add the stock in this way, until all the stock has been absorbed and the rice cooked.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6000, 910, 'Season with salt and pepper.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6001, 910, 'Sprinkle with chopped spring onion.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6002, 911, 'Using an electric mixer, beat mascarpone cheese, pumpkin puree, honey, cumin, ginger, cinnamon and salt until smooth. Set aside.Swirl a bit of olive oil in a pan over medium high heat. When oil is hot enough, add garlic and onions, tossing until coated. Slide in sausage and mushrooms and cook down until sausage has browned fully, approximately 10-12 minutes. Break up sausage as it cooks.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6003, 911, 'Remove from heat and stir in sage. Set aside.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6004, 911, 'Spread a thin layer of olive oil over the bottom and sides of a deep 9x13 baking dish.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6005, 911, 'Add about 1/4 cup of pumpkin mascarpone spread to the bottom of the dish and spread evenly to both sides. Top with three lasagna noodles, followed by another layer of mascarpone spread, a handful of spinach, a bit of the sausage and vegetables and a handful of shredded mozzarella. Repeat until all of the ingredients have been used.Top the final layer with the fresh mozzarella pieces and cover the dish with aluminum foil.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6006, 911, 'Bake for 30-35 minutes at 375 degrees. Uncover and bake another 5-10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6007, 912, 'Bring out your Crockpot/Slow Cooker and line it with your handy, dandy plastic liner.Throw the frozen chicken breast, chicken broth, and hoisin sauce into the Crockpot.Set to high and cook for four hours or until the chicken comes apart easily with a fork.Shred chicken, then drain excess liquid. (Can be made up to one day ahead).', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6008, 912, 'Combine yeast and warm water in a medium-sized mixing bowl.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6009, 912, 'Add 1 teaspoons of salt, two cups of flour, and knead until smooth (about 5-8 minutes).Cover and set aside.Preheat oven to 425 Fahrenheit.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6010, 912, 'Roll out dough into a large disk  inches thick on parchment paper.Move dough and paper to baking sheet.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6011, 912, 'Combine sauce ingredients in a blender and process until smooth.In a separate bowl, combine chicken, bell pepper, carrot, and broccoli with 4 tablespoons of pizza sauce.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6012, 912, 'Mix until uniformly covered with sauce.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6013, 912, 'Spread remaining sauce evenly over dough.Top with cheese, chicken, green onions, cilantro, and sesame seeds.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6014, 912, 'Bake for 17 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the crust is golden brown.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6015, 913, 'Slice mozzarella and tomatoes into 1/4 inch slices and arrange on platter', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6016, 913, 'Sprinkle basil leaves over all', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6017, 913, 'Drizzle with oil and vinegar', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6018, 913, 'Salt and pepper to taste', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6019, 914, 'Make dough by mixing egg & sour cream in a bowl, mix in flour until a shaggy rough dough forms, then add splash of milk to make it come together.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6020, 914, 'Begin mixing & kneading with your hands on a counter top, adding flour until the dough is no longer overly sticky and can be rolled out without tearing or breaking.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6021, 914, 'Mix all ingredients of the filling together.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6022, 914, 'Roll out dough to a long thin rectangle.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6023, 914, 'Along one side of the rectangle, place small scoops of the filling about 1-2 inches apart in a row.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6024, 914, 'Wet the dough with the water around each scoop of filling.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6025, 914, 'Take the opposite side of the rectangular dough and fold it over on top of the scoops, then removing as much air from each ravioli as possible, cut into squares or rounds, ensuring each ravioli is sealed thoroughly.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6026, 914, 'Repeat with the rest of the ravioli.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6027, 914, 'Cook ravioli in small batches in boiling water for 3 minutes, flip over and boil for another 3 minutes.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6028, 914, 'Meanwhile, heat a skillet over medium low heat and add butter.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6029, 914, 'Keep a close eye on the butter, skimming the foam off the top and cooking until it\'s a golden brown color.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6030, 914, 'Add sage and stir.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6031, 914, 'Add boiled ravioli and cook for a few minutes per side.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6032, 914, 'Serve, topping with a drizzle of the browned butter sauce over top and enjoy!', 14, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6033, 915, 'In a medium-sized bowl, mix salt, pepper and flour together.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6034, 915, 'Wash chicken and remove excess skin. Dredge in flour mixture and shake off excess.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6035, 915, 'Heat oil is a large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6036, 915, 'Add chicken and brown on all sides.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6037, 915, 'Remove from the pan and drain on paper towels.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6038, 915, 'To the same skillet add the onion and garlic and stir until onion is soft, but not browned. Next, add red pepper and mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally until softened.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6039, 915, 'Add tomatoes, white wine and oregano and cook until alcohol has burned off; 3-5 minutes.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6040, 915, 'Return chicken to skillet, cover and simmer on low for one hour.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6041, 916, 'In a skillet cook the garlic, onion, red pepper flakes, thyme, and salt and pepper to taste in the oil over moderately-low heat, stirring, until the onion is softened. Reserve 3 tablespoons of the onion mixture in a bowl. To the onions in the skillet, add the bell peppers and the broth, and simmer the mixture, covered, for 10 minutes, or until the peppers are very soft. In a blender puree the mixture until it is smooth, return it to the skillet, and swirl in the butter. Stir in the basil, lemon juice, and Cook the lasagne noodles according to package directions, rinse with cold water and drain.Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. In a bowl with the reserved cooked onions, combine 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella, ricotta, freshly grated nutmeg to taste, spinach and salt and pepper.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6042, 916, 'Mix well.Spoon 1 cup of sauce into an ungreased 9- by 9- by 2-inch baking pan.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6043, 916, 'Spread 3 tablespoons of filling on each noodle, roll up as for a jelly roll, and place seam-side down in the pan. Repeat until all the noodle are used. Top with remaining sauce, cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and bake uncovered, until golden, about 5 more minutes.This recipe yields 6 servings.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:37', '2023-04-25 06:26:37'),
(6044, 917, 'Cook chicken breasts (I sauteed mine with a little olive oil and salt and pepper) and set aside. Cook pasta while cooking the chicken and set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6045, 917, 'In a sauce pan, melt butter.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6046, 917, 'Add flour and stir in with butter, cook for 1 minute.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6047, 917, 'Whisk in milk, salt and pepper, garlic powder, lemon juice, and wine. Bring to a boil, constantly whisking. Reduce the heat and simmer for about 5 more minutes. Sauce should thicken.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6048, 917, 'In a large saute pan, add pasta, chicken, and any other desired additions.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6049, 917, 'Heat pan on medium heat.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6050, 917, 'Add alfredo sauce and toss with pasta.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6051, 917, 'Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and additional salt and pepper (if needed) and serve!Notes: This recipe made more sauce than I really needed, but I liked having extra. This way, you can add as much sauce as you prefer!', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6052, 918, 'Preheat the oven to 400* F. Grease an ovenproof dish or pan with butter or nonstick spray.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6053, 918, 'Spread the butternut in a single layer in the bottom of the prepared dish. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with olive oil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6054, 918, 'Bake in the preheated oven for about 20 minutes until soft.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6055, 918, 'Cut the chicken breasts into pieces and saut in olive oil in a pan for a few minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6056, 919, '- Preheat oven to 375F- Over medium heat, add oil on a skillet. When heated, brown ground chicken for few minutes.-', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6057, 919, 'Add onions and bell pepper.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6058, 919, 'Let them sweat for couple minutes and add black beans, jalapeno and stir them together. Continue this for 2-3 minutes.-', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6059, 919, 'Add all the spices and 1/4 cup enchilada sauce. Allow it to cook for few minutes then remove from heat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6060, 919, 'Let it cool for few minutes or leave it in the refrigerator for quick chill.- In a baking dish, pour about 2-3 tablespoon enchilada sauce then one tortilla.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6061, 919, 'Spread 1 tablespoon of sauce over the tortilla then spoon chicken-bean mixture followed by 1 tablespoon of cheese or more if you like.-', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6062, 919, 'Layer it likewise with the remaining tortillas. Just make sure the tortillas are well covered in sauce otherwise it will be very dry.- Top the last tortilla with remaining sauce and cheese.-', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6063, 919, 'Bake it covered for 10-12 minutes or until the sauce bubbles and cheese is melted completely.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6064, 920, 'In a large pot, bring salted water to a boil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6065, 920, 'Peel, deseed, and cut butternut squash in 1/4” cubes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6066, 920, 'Cook butternut squash cubes for 10 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6067, 920, 'Drain and roughly mash with a fork, season with curry powder, and set aside.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6068, 920, 'Place pan back on burner and melt butter over medium heat.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6069, 920, 'Cook shallots until translucent (and delicious smelling), about 2 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6070, 920, 'Add olive oil, wait a minute for it to heat up, then add rice and garlic, and constantly stir for 1 minute.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6071, 920, 'Add mushrooms and stir for another minute. Now is a good time to season with salt and pepper, but be careful...the stock contains salt, the cheese is salty, and the butternut squash was cooked in salt water. If you want to be safe, only season at the very end before serving.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6072, 920, 'Add one cup of stock and stir occasionally until most of the liquid is absorbed.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6073, 920, 'Then, add second cup of stock and stir occasionally until most of the liquid is absorbed.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6074, 920, 'Add mashed butternut squash, cheese, and herbs, stir, and add remaining stock.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6075, 920, 'Keep stirring, and after a total rice cooking time of about 20 minutes, the rice should be al dente and you’ll have a creamy, fantastic smelling risotto that can&#x27;t wait to be served on pre-warmed dishes.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6076, 920, 'Garnish with herbs and some more cheese, if you like. Then sit back, relax, and enjoy the ride.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6077, 921, 'In a large sauce pan on medium heat start browning your meat.On medium heat in a separate pan with the Tbsp of olive oil start to cook the onion, garlic, Italian seasoning, and basil for about 6-8 minutes, or until onion is translucent.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6078, 921, 'Add this to the meat mixture, along with the tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, black pepper, and 2 tbsp of the fresh parsley. Allow to simmer uncovered for 1 hour.Bring a large pot of water to boil and begin cook the lasagna noodles for 8-10 minutes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6079, 921, 'Drain and rinse with cold water.In a small mixing bowl combine remaining parsley, ricotta cheese, egg,  tsp salt and mix well.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6080, 921, 'Heat oven to 37', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6081, 921, 'Pour some meat sauce into the bottom of a 9 x 13 glass baking dish.To make the roll ups place a noodle onto a flat surface and spread with the cheese mixture. Then sprinkle a little parmesan reggiano cheese on the cheese mixture.Then roll them up!Once you have all of the lasagna roll ups lined into the dish, cover each with a little more of the meat mixture. Top with a slice of mozzarella cheese and then cover the dish with foil.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6082, 921, 'Bake in the oven for 20 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6083, 921, 'Remove foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes uncovered.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6084, 921, 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 10 minutes before serving.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6085, 922, 'Preheat oven to 42', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6086, 922, 'Position an oven rack in the next to lowest setting.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6087, 922, 'Place a 16-inch pizza pan on the rack.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6088, 922, 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6089, 922, 'Add olive oil to pan, and swirl to coat.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6090, 922, 'Add 2 cups onion and thyme to pan; cook for 3 minutes or until the onion is tender, stirring occasionally.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6091, 922, 'Add eggplant, bell pepper and garlic to pan; cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6092, 922, 'Add corn, salt, and black pepper to pan; cook for 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6093, 922, 'Roll dough into a 16-inch circle on a lightly floured surface.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6094, 922, 'Remove pan from oven. Coat the pan with cooking spray.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6095, 922, 'Place dough on pan. Arrange mozzarella slices evenly over dough.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6096, 922, 'Spread the corn mixture evenly over cheese, and top with Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6097, 922, 'Bake for 23 minutes. Arrange tomatoes evenly over pizza; bake an additional 5 minutes or until crust is browned.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6098, 922, 'Remove from oven; sprinkle with basil.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6099, 923, 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat, adding 1-2 tbsp olive oil', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6100, 923, 'Peel eggplant and cut into roughly 1/3 inch slices', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6101, 923, 'Whisk one egg in a shallow dish, and place breadcrumbs in another shallow dish', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6102, 923, 'Dip one slice of eggplant in egg and cover both sides', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6103, 923, 'Let excess egg drip off, and dredge eggplant slice in breadcrumbs', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6104, 923, 'Place in heated skillet and cook until golden brown on both sides', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6105, 923, 'Repeat for remaining eggplant, adding a tbsp of olive oil to the skillet between each batch if necessary.For the pesto, combine washed basil, pine nuts, Parmesan, garlic and 3 tbsp olive oil in a food processor', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6106, 923, 'Blend until a smooth paste is formed.To form stacks, layer eggplant, tomato and mozzarella in desired arrangement.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6107, 923, 'Add a layer of pesto between two layers, or top stacks with the pesto.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6108, 924, 'In a small sauce pan, bring balsamic vinegar to a simmer over medium high heat, simmer until the vinegar is reduced to 1/4 c. Set aside to cool. Preheat oven to 375 degrees f.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6109, 924, 'Slice the top 1/2-inch off of each tomato (reserve tops) and using a sharp spoon or a melon baller (I used an inexpensive aluminum tablespoon-sized measuring spoon) scoop out the cores and seeds from the tomatoes into a fine mesh strainer set over a bowl to catch the juices. Using your hands, break up and squeeze the pulp from the tomatoes to extract as much liquid as possible. Reserve 2/3 c. of the tomato juice (if needed add enough water to the juices to equal the 2/3 c.). In a small bowl combine the sugar and 1 1/2 t. kosher salt and sprinkle evenly inside the tomatoes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6110, 924, 'Lay the tomatoes cut-side down on a plate and set aside for 30 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6111, 924, 'Heat 2 T. olive oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat until the oil is shimmering.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6112, 924, 'Add the couscous and cook, stirring constantly until the couscous is coated in the oil and beginning to brown, about 2-3 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6113, 924, 'Add the garlic and pepper flakes, stir until evenly dispersed and fragrant.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6114, 924, 'Add the reserved tomato juice and remove from the heat, cover and let sit until the couscous is rehydrated, about 7 minutes. Gently fluff with a fork, stir in the lemon juice, basil and 3/4 c. Parmesan. Season with salt & pepper to taste. Then fold in the diced mozzarella.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6115, 924, 'After the tomatoes have sat for 30 minutes, blot the insides of the tomatoes dry with paper towels.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6116, 924, 'Sprinkle the cavities lightly with salt & pepper. Fill the tomatoes with the stuffing.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6117, 924, 'Drizzle the remaining 2 T. olive oil in a 13x9-inch baking dish.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6118, 924, 'Add the tomatoes to the baking dish.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6119, 924, 'Combine the 1/2 c. shredded mozzarella and the remaining 2 T. Parmesan, sprinkle over the tops of the tomatoes. Season the reserved tomato tops with salt & pepper and place in the empty spaces in the baking dish.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6120, 924, 'Bake until the tomatoes are softened but still hold their shape and the cheese on top is spotty-brown, 20-25 minutes.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6121, 924, 'Serve the tomatoes, drizzled with the balsamic reduction.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6122, 925, 'Heat the oil in a very large pan that has a close fitting lid.  Then add the celery, bacon, onion, carrot and garlic.  Fry this off for about 5 to 7 minutes until it has softened a little.  No colour is needed on the vegetables, so make sure the heat isnt too high that they become brown, but high enough the vegetables sweat and soften.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6123, 925, 'Add the tomato pure and  the thyme leaves, stir through and cook for about 30 seconds.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6124, 925, 'Add the stock, the tin of tomatoes, fresh tomatoes, and a little salt and pepper. Stir everything through, set the heat so that your soup is on a gentle simmer, cover and cook for about 25 minutes or until the vegetables are cooked al dente.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6125, 925, 'Add the pasta and cook until the pasta is ready.  Follow the timing instructions on the packet, but this is normally about 7 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6126, 925, 'Add the cabbage and the beans and cook until the cabbage has wilted.  This will take about 5 minutes.Check for seasoning and add some salt and pepper if needed before serving.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6127, 925, 'Sprinkle a little parmesan over each bowl of soup.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6128, 926, 'Preheat oven to 350 F. Generously coat skins of potatoes with oil (will make skin crispy).', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6129, 926, 'Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6130, 926, 'While potatoes are baking in the oven chop & mix together the red onion, tomato, garlic, fresh basil & cheese in a small bowl. Set aside.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6131, 926, 'When potatoes are done cut small slices off the top of each potato, scoop out the soft flesh and place in a large bowl.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6132, 926, 'Place empty shells on a baking sheet and turn oven down to 150 F.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6133, 926, 'Mix and mash in cultured dairy, butter & olive oil.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6134, 926, 'Pour bruschetta mixture in and stir well. Season to taste with sea salt and pepper.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6135, 926, 'Spoon the bruschetta potato mixture back into the shells and return them to the oven to keep warm. If potatoes are not reheated to a high temperature, the enzymes in the dairy will be preserved.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6136, 927, 'Pre heat oven to 350 degrees', 1, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6137, 927, 'Coat a 9X12 Lasagna pan with non stick spray', 2, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6138, 927, 'Drain ricotta cheese in a sieve while preparing onions and mushrooms.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6139, 927, 'On medium heat, saut onion on  in 2 tablespoons virgin olive oil until translucent; about 10 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6140, 927, 'Transfer to large mixing bowl.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6141, 927, 'In a large frying pan over medium/high heat saut portabella mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons olive oil until softened; about 5 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6142, 927, 'Add to the onions.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6143, 927, 'Beat the two eggs and mix with the ricotta cheese.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
(6144, 927, 'Mix the ricotta egg mixture into, onions and mushrooms and then the well drained spinach.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:26:38', '2023-04-25 06:26:38'),
