(7626, 1151, 'Place the pork, fat side up, in the slow cooker. Using a fork, pierce the roast all over and pour the liquid smoke over it to coat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
(7627, 1151, 'Sprinkle the sea salt evenly over the roast and cover. Cook on low for 10 hours (the roast is done when the meat begins to fall apart when shredded with a fork.)In a small saucepan, whisk together the pineapple juice, rice vinegar, honey, chili sauce and hoisin sauce. Bring the mixture to a boil and cook the sauce until reduced by half stirring with a heat resistant spatula frequently. Set aside.When the roast is done, transfer to a cutting board and shred the meat using two forks. Return the shredded meat back to the slow cooker and serve immediately with the sauce.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
(7628, 1152, 'Heat oven to 42', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
(7629, 1152, 'Prepare a cookie sheet, and then line the coated green beans onto the sheet.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
(7630, 1152, 'Bake in oven for 12-15 minutes, turning the beans, and then baking for another 5 minutes. (Start checking the coating after the first 12 minutes periodically to make sure that they are not burning.)', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
(7631, 1152, 'Remove from oven when they have reached a lightly crisp golden brown color.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:58', '2023-04-25 06:32:58'),
