(7718, 1168, 'Add remaining coconut oil and saute broccoli for 3  4 minutes until crisp-tender.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7719, 1168, 'Add chicken broth or water as needed to keep pan from becoming too dry.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7720, 1168, 'Add beef and sauce into the pan with the broccoli and stir until sauce thickens, 4  5 minutes.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7721, 1168, 'Serve over rice.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7722, 1169, 'Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Don\'t overwork it - just combine enough to have it well mixed.Form 4-6 round patties. Cook on med-high heat until done. If unsure, insert a thermometer - 165 F is the temp. you are aiming for.For roasted red pepper rings, seed and slice red pepper, spritz with olive oil and bake at 425 for 20 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7723, 1170, 'In a medium bowl, stir together the crushed tomatoes, diced tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, paprika, brown sugar, and salt. Set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7724, 1170, 'Place the carrots, celery, onions, garlic, beef, and kidney beans into the base of a slow cooker.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7725, 1170, 'Pour the tomato sauce mixture evenly over the top of the beef and vegetables. Cover and cook on high for 6 hours.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7726, 1170, 'Taste and adjust seasoning as necessary- adding more chili powder if you\'d prefer more spice.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7727, 1171, 'Slice open the dried ancho and chipotle chili and remove the seeds/pith.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7728, 1171, 'Place the dried chili peppers in a warm skillet (medium heat) and press them flat with a spatula to toast them for a few seconds per side until fragrant (be careful not to burn them!). Be sure to wear gloves or wash your hands directly after handling the chili peppers.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7729, 1171, 'Remove the dried chili and put them in a bowl or sauce pan.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7730, 1171, 'Pour 250 ml boiling water over it and leave it to soak for at least 15 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7731, 1171, 'In a large pot, saute the chopped bell pepper, onion, and mushrooms over medium heat.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7732, 1171, 'Meanwhile, fry the beef in a hot skillet until crispy.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7733, 1171, 'While the beef is frying, blend the chili peppers you\'ve been soaking with the soaking liquid.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7734, 1171, 'Add the beef to the large pot filled with the sauteed vegetables.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7735, 1171, 'Add the tomato sauce and blended chili peppers to the pot. If it is not enough liquid, add beef or vegetable broth (the other 250 ml water and 5 grams bouillon powder, unless you have \"real\" broth on hand) until everything is covered.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7736, 1171, 'Season with salt, pepper, cumin, and oregano to taste.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7737, 1171, 'Simmer for about 45 minutes or until thick enough.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7738, 1171, 'Serve with fresh cilantro.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7739, 1172, 'Heat a large heavy pan (with a tight fitting lid) over medium high heat. Once hot, add a few TBSP of oil and brown the beef in batches.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7740, 1172, 'Add more oil as needed. Take care not to overcrowd the meat so that it doesn\'t steam. You want a nice color on it  color means flavor so don\'t skimp on this part! Keep the batches of browned beef in a bowl and do not drain, you want all the juices from the meat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7741, 1172, 'Once all the meat is browned and removed from the pan, turn the heat down to medium, then add the onions and garlic and a little more oil if needed.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7742, 1172, 'Saute the onions and garlic gently. You don\'t want to brown them. Once they have softened, turn the heat up to medium high again, pile the onions and garlic in the middle of the pan and add the spices on top (cumin/coriander/paprika/chili powder) to the pan. Stir the spices into the onions until you can smell them (just a few seconds).', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7743, 1172, 'Add in the flour, oregano and the meat along with any juices to the pan and stir to combine. Carefully pour in the water/stock cube mixture and stir well.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7744, 1172, 'Bring to a boil, turn down the heat to a simmer and put the lid on. Simmer covered for 1 to 1.5 hours, checking and stirring every 20 to 30 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7745, 1172, 'Once the meat just starts to go tender add the beans and tomatoes, stir well, cover and cook for a further half hour or until the meat is so tender it easily breaks apart with a fork.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7746, 1172, 'Taste and season with salt & pepper as needed.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7747, 1172, 'Serve over what ever you want with what ever you want on top!', 9, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7748, 1173, 'Heat oven to 40', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7749, 1173, 'Add chicken, onion, pepper, bread crumbs, and ranch seasoning to a mixing bowl.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7750, 1173, 'Mix ingredients well.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7751, 1173, 'Scoop and make 3 large burger patties.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7752, 1173, 'Place in skillet and cook on medium low heat to sear juices and brown the patties.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7753, 1173, 'Place skillet with patties into the oven and bake for 15 minutes, or until patties are cooked thoroughly.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7754, 1173, 'Serve with your favorite toppings.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7755, 1174, 'Fry up 4 strips of bacon and set aside.Leave some of the bacon fat in the pan but remove from the eye.Put all of the spices and sauces into the ground beef, mix well and form even patties.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7756, 1174, 'Heat a large non-stick skillet until the pan (with some of the bacon fat in it) is hot.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7757, 1174, 'Place patties in hot pan and sear for 1 minute and 30 seconds each side. After searing the burgers, remove them from stove top and bake off in the oven at 415 degrees until it reaches your desired temperature (3-4 minutes).While the burgers are in the oven, get your egg going. On the same hot eye where you did your burger, use a new non-stick pan for the eggs. On the two over easy eggs, grind 2 grinds of salt, 2 grinds of pepper and a dash of Tabasco onto each egg yolk.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7758, 1174, 'Add the cheese on the burgers when the burgers have about 1 minute of cook time remaining, so the cheese melts.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7759, 1175, 'In a large skillet over medium-high heat, add spray with a generous amount of PAM and add oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7760, 1175, 'Add mustard seeds and saute for 30 seconds-till you hear popping noises.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7761, 1175, 'Add curry leaves- BE CAREFUL, they pop hot oil!', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7762, 1175, 'Add onions and peppers- sweat for about 30 seconds.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7763, 1175, 'Add chopped garlic, chilies and turmeric.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7764, 1175, 'Saute for about 5-7 minutes, until the onions and peppers are soft.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7765, 1175, 'Add peas and carrots mixture, cumin powder and salt.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7766, 1175, 'Saute for about 7-10 minutes- you want all the veggies to be soft and cooked through.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7767, 1175, 'Meanwhile in a small bowl, add the cubed tofu, a pinch of turmeric, cumin powder, coarse black pepper and some cayenne pepper (totally optional!).', 9, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7768, 1175, 'Mix and set aside to marinate for a bit.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7769, 1175, 'Once the veggies are cooked, add the tofu- saute until slightly brown and soft enough that it crumbles.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7770, 1175, 'Add juice form half a lemon and half of the chopped cilantro.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7771, 1175, 'Mix and add the diced boiled potato, and toss until everything is coated, soft and taste for salt/spices. Using a masher, mash the mixture until mushy and until the veggies are small. Set aside to cool. Once cooled, add a bit of the breadcrumbs and mix with your hands. Start forming into thick patties (mixture should make 4). If its still giving you a hard time, add more breadcrumbs. Make 4 patties, place on a plate and wrap with plastic wrap until ready to use.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7772, 1175, 'In a small skillet sprayed with PAM over medium-high heat, add one patty at a time. Cook for about 2 minutes on each side- until browned and crispy.At the same time, saute the thick slices of onion, until charred and slightly soft.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7773, 1175, 'Spread a generous amount of the chutney spread on each side on the bread, place burger, onions tomato and cilantro leaves.', 15, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7774, 1175, 'Serve with a slice of lemon and reduced-fat chips on the side.', 16, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7775, 1176, 'Heat grill. Coat the chicken breasts liberally with the jerk seasoning and cook the chicken on both sides until cooked through, approximately 10 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7776, 1176, 'Transfer to a plate and cover with foil. Allow the chicken to rest for 10 minutes while you prepare the rest of the salad.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7777, 1176, 'In a large bowl, add the torn romaine hearts and top with the bell pepper, mango, avocado, bacon and scallions.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7778, 1176, 'Cut the chicken into cubes and add to the salad.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7779, 1176, 'Sprinkle the salad with the macadamia nuts and serve with the Fire-Roasted Pineapple Vinaigrette on the side or serve with your favorite dressing.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7780, 1177, 'Bring a pot of water to a boil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7781, 1177, 'Add salt and add macaroni and cook until not quite al dente (macaroni will continue to cook in the oven).In another pot melt the butter, add the flour and stir with a whisk or a wooden spoon for a couple of minutes to cook the flour.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7782, 1177, 'Add the milk, 1/2 cup at a time whisking until the mixture thickens, then add remaining milk and let cook over low heat until the sauce thickens, stirring constantly, scraping from the bottom of the pan and being careful not to burn it at the bottom.When the sauce is thick add the grated cheeses and stir until melted. Stir in the nutmeg, hot pepper sauce and salt, remove from heat and set aside.When the macaroni is cooked drain into colander and return to the pot.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7783, 1177, 'Pour the cheese sauce over the macaroni and stir with a wooden spoon.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7784, 1177, 'Pour the macaroni into individual gratins or a large buttered baking dish. You can add a few tomato slices into the macaroni either half way through pouring it into the pan or at the end, tucking them in with a knife. Don\'t smooth out the top, allow a few peaks here and there, they will become crisp and delicious as you bake it.To make the topping:Melt the butter, pour over the bread crumbs in a bowl and mix to combine.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7785, 1178, 'Brown the lean ground beef in a deep skillet. Cook over medium heat until cooked all the way through, and then drain.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7786, 1178, 'In a large pan over high heat add in all of your additional ingredients: cooked ground beef, tomato juice, kidney beans, pinto beans, water, tomato paste, chili powder, cumin, black pepper, oregano, sugar, cayenne pepper, bell pepper, and chopped onions. Bring to a boil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7787, 1178, 'Once your large pot of chili has started to boil, lower the heat and simmer for 2 hours uncovered.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7788, 1179, 'Make a rub by combining the paprika, garlic powder, chili powder, oregano, and ground cumin in a medium sized bowl. Set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7789, 1179, 'Place the ground chicken in a large bowl and add the chopped sun dried tomatoes, chopped garlic, juice and zest of 1 lemon, chopped cilantro, salt, pepper, grated Parmesan, chopped scallions, and olive oil.Shape the burgers into a ball and roll in the rub; then flatten the burgers to desired thickness.Grill burger until juices run clear. The cooking time depends on the thickness of the burger.Prepare the dressing by combining the mustard, balsamic vinegar, honey, 1/4 tsp salt, and 1/4 tsp pepper in a small bowl and whisk.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7790, 1179, 'Serve burgers with lettuce, tomato, and cucumber drizzled with honey mustard dressing. Feel free to drizzle some over the burger as well!', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7791, 1180, 'Preheat oven to 42', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7792, 1180, 'Place tomatillos, onion, peppers, jalapeno and garlic in a large roasting pan.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7793, 1180, 'Sprinkle with olive oil and roast for 30 minutes, or until vegetables have softened.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7794, 1180, 'Let vegetables cool. (Note: if the skin on the pasilla peppers isnt blistered, place under broiler for 5-10 more minutes to make peeling the skin off easier.)', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7795, 1180, 'Peel the skin of the pasilla peppers and then place all vegetables in a food processor. Pulse until just chopped up.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7796, 1180, 'Heat olive oil in a large pot and add spices.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7797, 1180, 'Heat until fragrant.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7798, 1180, 'Add turkey and cook until just browned. Deglaze with the pale ale.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7799, 1180, 'Add chicken stock and vegetables from food processor. Cook for 45 min-1 hour or until thickened. And beans and continue to cook for 1/2 hour longer.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7800, 1180, 'Add in frozen corn and stir to combine. Take off heat and let cool.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7801, 1180, 'Serve with cilantro and sour cream.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7802, 1181, 'Mix the mayonnzise, roasted red peppers and a clove of garlic in a food processor until creamy to make the aoili and set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7803, 1181, 'Mix together all remaining ingredients except the salmon, then gently fold in the salmon and shape into patties.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7804, 1181, 'Pan sear patties in a non-stick skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on one side, then turn the burgers, lower the heat to medium low, cover, and cook until done, about 5 minutes more.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7805, 1181, 'Serve the salmon burgers without a bun with a healthy dollop of the Roasted Red Pepper Aioli and a mound of shredded cucumber on top or serve on a traditional bun with condiments of your choice.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7806, 1182, 'Shuck your corn and using a knife, carefully cut the kernels off the cobs. Set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7807, 1182, 'In a large Dutch oven or stock pot, heat olive oil to medium high and add the chopped sweet potato.  Saut about 10 minutes before adding the onion.  Saut an additional 8 minutes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7808, 1182, 'Add just a splash of the vegetable stock while the sweet potato and onion are sauting to give them a little steam.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7809, 1182, 'Add the chopped bell pepper and saut another 5 minutes, again adding a splash of vegetable stock to steam the veggies.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7810, 1182, 'Add the diced tomatoes, drained beans, corn kernels and the remaining veggie stock. Stir.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(7811, 1182, 'Add all of the seasonings (chili powder, oregano, salt, cocoa powder, cinnamon, cumin, red pepper, black pepper).  Stir to combine all ingredients. Bring the chili to a boil then reduce the heat to medium low and cover. Allow the chili to simmer for 30 minutes before serving it in heaping bowls with your favorite toppings!', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7812, 1182, 'See original recipe: http://www.perrysplate.com/2011/01/vegetarian-sweet-potato-chili.html', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7813, 1183, 'Brown both meats in a Dutch oven or large pot over medium-high heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7814, 1183, 'Add 2 cups of water and bring to a boil. Discard fatty oil either by draining or with a strainer.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7815, 1183, 'Add about 4 cups of new water and bring to a boil for 10 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7816, 1183, 'Add remaining ingredients; keep at a boil for another 10 minutes. Reduce heat to low, and simmer, slightly uncovered, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until beef is tender.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7817, 1183, 'Serve with rice or/and desired toppings like diced onions, cheese, or crackers.*Instead of using pre-made chili mix packets (like we do), you can also combine the following ingredients to make your own chili seasoning: chili powder, cumin, oregano, cayenne pepper, and salt.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7818, 1184, 'Turn on the pressure cooker and place on sauté mode. Once heated, add the olive oil, onion, and bell pepper. Sauté for 3 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7819, 1184, 'Add in the ground beef and continue to stir until the beef is thoroughly cooked.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7820, 1184, 'Add in the seasonings. Stir.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7821, 1184, 'Add crushed tomatoes and kidney beans and mix well.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7822, 1184, 'Pour in chicken broth and macaroni noodles. Stir the mixture until well combined.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7823, 1184, 'Hit the cancel button on the Instant Pot.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7824, 1184, 'Securely place the lid on the pressure cooker and lock the lid in place. Set the vent to seal and start the manual cook time for 4 minutes.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7825, 1184, 'Once the cooking time is finished, carefully place the valve to vent and allow the pressure pin to drop before unlocking the lid to the Instant Pot.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7826, 1184, 'Remove the lid and stir the chili mac recipe well.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7827, 1184, 'Mix in the cheese.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7828, 1184, 'Add your favorite toppings and serve.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7829, 1185, 'Heat oil in Dutch oven over high heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7830, 1185, 'Add onions and carrots, stirring to cook until carrots are fork tender.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7831, 1185, 'Add the garlic, cumin and taco seasoning stirring to coat veggies.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7832, 1185, 'Add chicken and cook over med-high heat until pieces are no longer pink on the outside.Stir in green pepper and cook for a few minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7833, 1185, 'Pour in a little of the chicken stock if you need to keep the chicken from sticking.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7834, 1185, 'Add the beans and chicken stock.Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat to let it simmer for 20-25 minutes.Note: We like a soupier chili in our house because everyone adds something to their own bowl, like crushed up crackers, sour cream or grated cheese. If you like a thicker chili, you can sprinkle a few tablespoons of flour over the onions and carrots at the same time that you add the seasonings.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7835, 1186, 'Cut the salmon into large hunks and run it through a food processor until no large pieces remain.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7836, 1186, 'Add to the salmon the soy sauce, garlic, ginger, oyster sauce, green onion, and basil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7837, 1186, 'Combine ingredients well and form 4 large patties from mixture.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
(7838, 1186, 'Heat up the sesame oil in a large frying pan on medium high heat and add in the patties. Cook for about 10 minutes flipping once half way through.To make the sauce, add together all the above listed ingredients and stir to combine.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:32:59', '2023-04-25 06:32:59'),
