(7958, 1205, 'Mix the eggs, milk, pumpkin, vanilla, brown sugar and spices into a dish for dipping. Dip the bread into the egg mixture until evenly coated on both sides, cooks on a grill heated to 350 degrees for about 2-3 minutes per side or until golden brown.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7959, 1205, 'Serve hot with butter and maple syrup or as we did with pumpkin butter.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7960, 1206, 'Place in a foil and bake for 20 minutes in a 375 degree ovenor until it is soft.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7961, 1206, 'Cook lentils in boiling water (15 to 25 minutes).', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7962, 1206, 'Cook brown rice.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7963, 1206, 'Throw carrots, onions, garlic, cooked eggplant and rice in a food processor and process together.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7964, 1206, 'After the lentils are cooked, add the processed veggies and rice in, smash together with your hands or with a potato masher.  Note: try not to smash all of the lentils.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7965, 1206, 'Add corn (optional), oats, flour, and seasonings.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7966, 1206, 'Make burger patties.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7967, 1206, 'Cover in corn meal.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7968, 1206, 'Cook in a little bit of oil until the outside is crunchy.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7969, 1206, 'Place in a whole wheat bun and add your favorite fix ins.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7970, 1206, 'Enjoy!', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7971, 1207, 'Preheat oven to 35', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7972, 1207, 'Melt 6 tbsp. butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7973, 1207, 'Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, for about 4 minutes.Stir in cayenne and season to taste with salt and pepper.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7974, 1207, 'Whisk in hot milk, 1/2 cup at a time, and cook, stirring, until sauce thickens. Reduce heat to low and stir in 2 cups of cheese. Cook, stirring, until cheese melts, about 2 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7975, 1207, 'Combine pasta and sauce in a large bowl, and season with salt.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7976, 1207, 'Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over the bottom of a buttered 8\"  11\" baking dish.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7977, 1207, 'Place one-third of the pasta in the baking dish, top with 1/2 cup of cheese, then repeat, layering pasta and cheese, ending with cheese, making three layers in all.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7978, 1207, 'Pour cream over assembled macaroni and cheese. Melt remaining butter in a skillet.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7979, 1207, 'Add bread crumbs, coat with melted butter, and sprinkle over macaroni and cheese.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7980, 1207, 'Bake until crust is golden, about 30 minutes. Allow to rest for 15 minutes before serving.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7981, 1208, 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7982, 1208, 'Place the carrot sticks in a large Tupperware bowl that has a tight-fitting lid.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7983, 1208, 'Pour oil and remaining ingredients into the bowl, on top of the carrot sticks.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7984, 1208, 'Secure the lid and shake the ingredients around vigorously until every last carrot stick is coated with flavor.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7985, 1208, 'Place the carrot sticks, in a single layer, on an ungreased cookie sheet.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7986, 1208, 'Bake for about 15 minutes. Check the carrot sticks, shake the pan, flip them around, whatever you need to do.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7987, 1208, 'Continue to bake for an additional 5-15 minutes, until carrot sticks are soft in the middle but nice and crunchy around the edges. Watch them closely.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7988, 1209, 'In small saucepan, combine soy sauce, mirin, brown sugar, and ginger; bring to boil over medium-high heat, whisking to dissolve sugar. Reduce until slightly syrupy, about 3 minutes. Adjust heat, if necessary, to prevent boil-over.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7989, 1209, 'Remove from heat and allow to cool completely. (Sauce may be prepared up to 2 days in advance and refrigerated in a covered container.)Bring large pot of water to boil. Cook spinach for 1 minute.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7990, 1209, 'Drain and transfer to cold water bath to stop the cooking.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7991, 1209, 'Drain again. Dry thoroughly between layers of paper towels. (Spinach may be prepared up to 2 days in advance and refrigerated in covered container.)In large bowl, combine turkey, scallions, sesame oil, reserved spinach, and 1 tablespoon of reserved sauce. Season with salt and pepper and blend well without overworking.Form turkey-spinach mixture into 4 patties, about 3\" across and 1\" thick.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7992, 1209, 'Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. When hot, add patties and cook about 5 minutes per side, until nicely browned and cooked through. Lower heat if necessary to prevent burning.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7993, 1209, 'Serve with some of the sauce spooned over.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7994, 1209, 'Garnish with the sliced scallions, if desired.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7995, 1210, 'Begin by Preheating oven to 350Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat, add in elbows and cook until pasta is al dente.While waiting for pasta to cook begin preparing your sauce. In a medium size sauce pan, melt butter over medium heat, add in nutritional yeast and mix together to form a paste', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7996, 1210, 'Add in soy milk, using a whisk combine together ingredients make sure your sauce is lump free, let simmer for 5 minute or until sauce begins to thicken', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7997, 1210, 'Add is pureed butternut squash, thoroughly mix together ingredients to ensure everything is well blended (you may notice that the butternut squash also helps to thicken the sauce).Stir in Cheese, let sit for 1 to 2 minutes or until sauce has a creamy velvety smooth consistency.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7998, 1210, 'Remove Sauce from heat and let sit', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(7999, 1210, 'Drain pasta and add pasta to the cheese sauce, stir together and pour mixture into a greased 9 x 9 baking pan', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8000, 1210, 'Sprinkle breadcrumbs over macaroni and cheese and let bake for 15 minutes or until cheese begins to bubble', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8001, 1210, 'Serve Warm and enjoy this creamy Vegan home-style comfort food!', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8002, 1211, 'Soak Pinto beans overnight in water, drain and rinse the next morning.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8003, 1211, 'Next add diced onions and tomatoes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8004, 1211, 'Add chili meat and seasoning packet along with onion powder and garlic powder, stir to mix. Then pour in beef broth. Two cups is plenty  you wont completely cover your beans and meat, but during cooking the meat will release quite a bit of juice and fat, adding to the liquid content. We want to make chili, not soup.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8005, 1211, 'Cook on high for two hours in the Crock Pot.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8006, 1211, 'Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce, stir to mix well. Reduce heat to low and continue to cook for 6-8 hours, stirring every couple of hours. Taste an hour or so before serving time and add salt and pepper if needed.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8007, 1211, 'I love to serve our chili with a batch of Christy Jordans Dixie Cornbread. Its the best cornbread Ive ever eaten.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8008, 1212, 'To prep the burgers:  In a medium bowl, toss in the ground meat, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, and Worcestershire sauce.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8009, 1213, 'I a wok or large skillet, heat 1 teaspoon sesame oil over medium-high heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8010, 1213, 'Add chicken and saute until cooked through. Set aside and cover.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8011, 1213, 'In the same pan, heat 1 teaspoon sesame oil over medium-high heat.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8012, 1213, 'Add bok choy stalks (not the leaves), carrots and snow peas and saute until just tender. Set aside and cover.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8013, 1213, 'Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine broth, sherry, cornstarch and Sriracha.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8014, 1213, 'Heat final teaspoon sesame oil over medium high heat and add garlic.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8015, 1213, 'Saute until fragrant, 30 seconds to 1 minute.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8016, 1213, 'Add sauce and bring to a boil. Stir until it thickens then add chicken, veggies, bok choy leaves and green onion. Stir until all are coated and heated through.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8017, 1214, 'Mix together chicken, onions, red pepper, cilantro, crushed red pepper, chili powder, lime juice, salt and pepper. I mixed together that morning and let sit in the fridge until dinner that night, about 8 hours. You dont have to do that, it just gives the meat some time to absorb all the flavor.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8018, 1214, 'Heat up the grill on Medium heat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8019, 1214, 'Form into 6 patties.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8020, 1214, 'Once grill is hot, add burgers and cook about 5-7 minutes on each side or until internal temperature reaches 165 degrees. Try not to move them around so you can get some grill marks.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8021, 1214, 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mash avocado with cumin, lime, salt and pepper to your desired guacamole consistency. I leave mine a little chunky.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8022, 1214, 'When burgers are finished, place on a bun and top with guacamole. We had this with a side of Spanish rice. So fresh and delicious!', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8023, 1214, 'Printable Recipe', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8024, 1214, 'Recipe adapted from The Housewife in Training Files', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8025, 1215, 'Add a swirl of olive oil to a skillet and add diced mushrooms and onions.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8026, 1215, 'Saute until softened then season with salt and pepper.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8027, 1215, 'Add drained black beans to a medium bowl and press and mash with a fork.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8028, 1215, 'Mix in mushrooms and onions then add egg and bread crumbs.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8029, 1215, 'Finally mix in cumin and chipotle chili powder.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8030, 1215, 'Roll and form into burger patties (sliders or full size).', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8031, 1215, 'Form a indent in the center of each burger', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8032, 1215, 'Add a spoonful of cream cheese spread to the indent in the burgers and then form the burger over the cream cheese.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8033, 1215, 'Heat a skillet over medium heat, add a swirl of olive oil.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8034, 1215, 'Add 2 burgers at a time and sear on each side until cooked and browned, about 4 minutes each side.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8035, 1215, 'If you want to add sliced cheese on top, add now and cover skillet to steam and melt cheese.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8036, 1215, 'Remove to a plate, then cook remaining patties.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8037, 1215, 'For the avocado creme, combine all ingredients in a food processor or blender, and mix until smooth. Taste and add more sour cream or lime juice if needed.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8038, 1215, 'To plate, add each hot cooked burger to an open toasted bun. Top with lettuce and tomato (optional) and a hearty scoop of avocado creme and then top with bun.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8039, 1216, 'Rub a medium wooden bowl with cut side of garlic clove and discard garlic; add lemon juice, mayonnaise, and cheese to bowl and stir to combine.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8040, 1216, 'Add remaining ingredients except lettuce and mix well; line serving platter with lettuce and top with chicken mixture.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8041, 1217, 'Make a batter with chili powder, beaten egg, flour, vegetable stock (or water) and salt. Dip cauliflower pieces in the batter and fry in oil until light brown.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8042, 1217, 'Heat oil in a pan and add chopped onions, ginger-garlic paste, green chillies, and curry leaves, and saute well.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8043, 1217, 'Add vegetable stock, soy sauce, chili sauce, and tomato sauce and stir well.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8044, 1217, 'Mix corn starch with water and add to pan.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8045, 1217, 'Add fried cauliflower pieces and salt and cook until dry. Stir in sugar.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8046, 1218, 'Oven: 350F.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8047, 1218, 'Grease a standard muffin pan (we like jumbo but not mini, they\'ll get to crispy).', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8048, 1218, 'Fry the bacon, remove and pat dry. The bacon should be crispy but without char- any chunks of fat that are still white should be discarded.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8049, 1218, 'Melt the unsweetened chocolate and butter in a double broiler.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8050, 1218, 'Cool slightly, then whisk in the sugar and salt.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8051, 1218, 'Add the eggs, one at a time.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8052, 1218, 'Sift the flour and cocoa together, then combine with the chocolate.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8053, 1218, 'Stir in the pieces of bacon and chocolate.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8054, 1218, 'Bake ~30 min., making sure to allow brownie cupcakes to cool before removing.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8055, 1219, 'Wipe/pat dry potatoes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8056, 1219, 'Mix in chili powder and salt.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8057, 1219, 'Heat oil and fry in batches till crunchy and crispy.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8058, 1219, 'Remove and keep aside.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8059, 1219, 'In the same oil, fry curry leaves till crispy too.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8060, 1219, 'Scoop out and add over chips.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8061, 1219, 'Crush and toss the leaves with the chips.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8062, 1220, 'Cut 1/2 of a pineapple into small cubes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8063, 1220, 'Add to food processor.Puree pineapple until liquified.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8064, 1220, 'Cut chicken into cubes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8065, 1220, 'Add to pan.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8066, 1220, 'Pour puree\'d pinapple over top. Cook chicken.Chop 1/2 onion.When chicken is almost fully cooked, add onion to chicken &amp; pineapple mixture.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8067, 1220, 'Add a scoop of Coconut Milk to chicken mixture.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8068, 1220, 'Add a tablespoon of white pepper.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8069, 1220, 'Add  4 cloves of pressed garlic.Grab a small bunch of cilantro and few sprigs of thyme. Chop them.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8070, 1220, 'Add cilantro and thyme to chicken mixture.Once chicken is fully cooked and onions are almost see through, scoop mixture into food processor. Lightly grind food until chicken looks shredded.Grate 2 medium sized carrots finely.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8071, 1220, 'Pour in a new pan 1 can of coconut milk, 32 oz. chicken broth, 1 can of water.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8072, 1220, 'Add 2 cans Great Northern Beans &amp; Shredded chicken mixture.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8073, 1220, 'Mix well. Bring to a boil. Then simmer.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8074, 1220, 'Add carrots.In another pan, add 1 cup of water. 1 tsp garlic, 1/4 tsp. cumin, 2 tbsp. coconut flakes, sea salt, 4 dashes of Jamaican Allspice.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8075, 1220, 'Add 1/2 cup Long Grain Brown Rice.Cook rice until al dente. (Still slightly crunchy.)', 14, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8076, 1220, 'Add rice to simmering mixture. Simmer until carrots and rice are cooked thoroughly.', 15, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8077, 1220, 'Serve with sour cream.', 16, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8078, 1221, 'Wasabi Dressing: 1/2 cup mayonnaise, 1/4 cup sour cream, 2 tablespoons wasabi paste or fresh grated wasabi cream -', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8079, 1221, 'Mix all ingredients well.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8080, 1221, 'Taste it and add a little wasabi paste more if you like it really spicy. This can be made ahead of time and last in the refrigerator for a week or more. I always make extra because it makes a great dip.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8081, 1222, 'In a wide-bottomed saucepan, add 1 tablespoon extra virgin coconut oil and set to low heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8082, 1222, 'Add the onions and cook for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally to caramelize. If the onions look dry, splash a bit of water into the pan.While waiting for the onions to cook, steam the parsnip. Set aside and let them cool.After that, prepare the green beans.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8083, 1222, 'Remove the ends of the beans and cut them into 2 inch pieces. Steam them for 8 minutes. Set them aside in an 8x8 baking dish.Once the onions have caramelized, set them aside. Cook the mushrooms in the same pan and saute for one minute.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8084, 1222, 'Add garlic. Stir for 5 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8085, 1222, 'Add half of the garlic and mushroom mixture to the green beans.Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8086, 1222, 'Put the other half of the garlic and mushroom mixture, as well as the steamed parsnips in a blender.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8087, 1222, 'Add the nutritional yeast, salt, pepper, and crushed red pepper.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8088, 1222, 'Pour the blended mixture over the mushrooms and green beans. Stir to coat. Use the caramelized onions as toppings.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8089, 1222, 'Bake for another 30 minutes.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8090, 1222, 'Serve.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8091, 1223, 'Slice Chavrie goat cheese log into 6 equal disks', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8092, 1223, 'In a large bowl, combine the ground turkey, eggs, garlic and a pinch each of salt and pepper.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8093, 1223, 'Mix gently to bring all the ingredients together; do not over mix.Form meat mixture into 12 patties. On 6 of the patties, gently place Chavrie disks onto patties, pressing down lightly.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8094, 1223, 'Place remaining patties on top, press, and seal edges to totally enclose filling, forming 6 total patties.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8095, 1223, 'Place patties on grill 4 minutes, until bottom is brown. Turn the burgers over and cook an additional 4 minutes, or until done to your preference.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8096, 1223, 'Place in rolls and serve with your favorite accompaniments', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8097, 1224, 'Preheat oven to 350 F.Spray an 8x8 inch pan with cooking spray. Set aside.In a food processor, puree kidney beans and beets.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8098, 1224, 'Transfer to a large bowl.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(8099, 1224, 'Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand until smooth and fully combined.Fold batter into the greased pan.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8100, 1224, 'Bake for 35-40 minutes, turning the pan halfway through.When the brownies are done, test them with a toothpick. You want some batter to cling to the toothpick. Do not over bake.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8101, 1224, 'Let cool completely. Refrigerate for one hour.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8102, 1224, 'Cut into squares or use cookie cutters to make heart shapes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8103, 1225, 'Whisk together the rub ingredients in a small bowl.2 If the roast is tied up with butcher string, untie it. Pat the roast dry with paper towels. Rub the spice mix into the roast all over, reserving any leftover spice mix for later.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8104, 1225, 'Let sit at room temperature at least one hour or chill overnight. 3', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8105, 1225, 'Heat vegetable oil in a frying pan on medium high heat. (If you are using a slow cooker with a removable container that can be used on the stovetop, use that, otherwise use a separate pan.)', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8106, 1225, 'Place the roast in the pan and brown on all sides.4', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8107, 1225, 'Place the roast in a slow cooker, and add any reserved spice rub. Cook on the low setting for 6 to 10 hours, until the pork is fall apart tender. 5', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8108, 1225, 'Remove the roast from the slow cooker and place on a cutting board.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8109, 1225, 'Cut into large chunks. Then use two forks to pull the meat apart into bite sized shreds. Return the shreds to the slow cooker and toss to coat with the juice from the roast. (Alternatively you can just shred the roast with two forks in the slow cooker itself.)', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8110, 1225, 'Serve with warm tortillas, avocados, shredded cabbage, sliced radishes, cilantro, and a splash of lime juice or salsa.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8111, 1226, 'Add all of the ingredients, EXCEPT the onions and the oil, to a food processor and blend until the mixture is firm and moldable.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8112, 1226, 'Transfer to a medium size bowl and stir in the onions.Measure out 1/3 of a cup of the mixture and roll into a ball, then flatten into a round patty.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8113, 1226, 'Heat 1 tablespoon of oil on medium-high heat in a large skillet.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8114, 1226, 'Add patties to the pan and cook until golden brown and then flip and cook the other side until golden brown.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8115, 1226, 'Add the other tablespoon of oil if needed.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8116, 1227, 'In a large bowl, carefully mix all of the ingredients except the breadcrumbs, seafood seasoning and butter. Form into 8 patties and set on a baking sheet. Chill for an hour.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8117, 1227, 'Once chilled, cover all sides of the patties with bread crumbs and lay on a separate baking sheet.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8118, 1227, 'Bake in an oven preheated to 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes, flipping once.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8119, 1227, 'If desired, top with a bit of butter and set the burgers onto a vegetable grill basket.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8120, 1227, 'Heat for 1-2 minutes on a preheated grill just for flavor and a little color.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8121, 1227, 'Serve on warm buns.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8122, 1228, 'Tofu and veggie scramble', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8123, 1228, 'Press the tofu for 30 minutes prior to cooking. Chop all the veggies and leave ready to begin cooking process.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8124, 1228, 'Using a non-stick skillet, heat olive oil on medium heat.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8125, 1228, 'Add pressed tofu and crumble in large pieces. The tofu will need to cook and dry out a little for 10 to 15 minutes, so meanwhile, add onions and garlic to tofu.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8126, 1228, 'After those 15 minutes, add asparagus and mushroom and all the rest of the spices plus the water. Cook for 5 minutes and serve hot!', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8127, 1228, 'Home Fries', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8128, 1228, 'Prepare potatoes before starting on tofu scramble.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8129, 1228, 'Preheat oven to 450F and move oven rack to the next to last highest row. Line a small cookie sheet with parchment paper.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8130, 1228, 'Wash and scrub potatoes. Dice them and add to a medium bowl.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8131, 1228, 'Add olive oil, salt and pepper and mix well.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8132, 1228, 'Pour potatoes on cookie sheet and spread evenly.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8133, 1228, 'Bake for 20 minutes and serve while hot.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8134, 1229, 'Prepare a Peanut Butter and Banana Sandwich', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8135, 1229, 'Mix whisked egg, orange juice, nutmeg and cinnamon and cayenne in a bowl', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8136, 1229, 'Heat a skillet and place One (', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8137, 1229, 'Tablespoon in same', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8138, 1229, 'Dip Sandwich in egg mixture coating both sides', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8139, 1229, 'Cook in skillet for one minute on each side', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8140, 1229, 'Ladle with syrup, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and garnish with more bananas', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8141, 1230, 'In a bowl, add chuck, sirloin, bread crumbs, steak sauce, eggs, salt, and pepper, and mix gently with fork.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8142, 1230, 'Form 4 patties out of this mixture.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8143, 1230, 'Cook the hamburgers patties on each side, then cover with aluminium foil.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8144, 1230, 'Cut the sides of the bun, then grill in a stove-top grill until toasted.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8145, 1230, 'Place patties and a slice of blue cheese in each bun.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8146, 1230, 'Serve hot.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8147, 1231, 'Wash and slice sweet potato length wise.Coat with oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8148, 1231, 'Sprinkle on the sea salt and ground chipotle peppers.On a baking sheet, roast sliced potatoes with skin at 400 degrees.Turn slices around ever 5 minutes or so until browned on all sides.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8149, 1231, 'Garnish with yogurt and pepitas \"sunflower seeds.\"', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8150, 1232, 'Wash and slice sweet potato length wise.Coat with oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8151, 1232, 'Sprinkle on the sea salt and ground chipotle peppers.On a baking sheet, roast sliced potatoes with skin at 400 degrees.Turn slices around ever 5 minutes or so until browned on all sides.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8152, 1232, 'Garnish with yogurt and pepitas \"sunflower seeds.\"', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8153, 1233, 'Defrost spinach and squeeze out excess water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8154, 1233, 'Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8155, 1233, 'Add garlic; saute 1 minute.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8156, 1233, 'Add salt and spinach; saute 3 minutes or until the spinach is warmed through.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8157, 1233, 'Place spinach mixture, basil, cream cheese, and pepper in a food processor; process until smooth. Spoon spinach mixture into a medium bowl.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8158, 1233, 'Add yogurt and Parmesan; stir to combine. Chill.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8159, 1233, 'Serve with pita chips.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8160, 1234, 'Brown the ground beef over medium heat, breaking into small pieces as it cooks.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8161, 1234, 'Add salt and pepper to taste while cooking.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8162, 1234, 'Remove the cooked meat from the heat, drain to remove grease (you can rinse well under hot water to remove the grease).', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8163, 1234, 'Transfer beef into large pot, or dutch oven, and add the remaining ingredients.  Stir together and cook over medium heat, bringing to a simmer.  Reduce the heat to low and continue simmering 50-60 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8164, 1235, 'Rinse the chicken quarters really well and place them in a stock pot.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8165, 1235, 'To the chicken in the pot, add the water (water should mostly cover the chicken), bouillon, bay leaf, onion, bell pepper and garlic.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8166, 1235, 'Place the stock pot over medium high heat and bring to a boil; reduce the heat to medium, cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, approximately 30 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8167, 1235, 'Remove pot from the heat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8168, 1235, 'Remove chicken quarters from the pot and transfer them to a cutting board and cool until they can be comfortably handled.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8169, 1235, 'Remove meat from the bones and chop it into small pieces then shred slightly; set aside.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8170, 1235, 'Remove approximately 1 cup (250ml) of the liquid from the stock pot and set aside.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8171, 1235, 'Return the stock pot to medium heat and bring to a simmer.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8172, 1235, 'Place the flour into a small bowl.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8173, 1235, 'While stirring constantly, gradually add the reserved liquid to the flour until a smooth paste is formed.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8174, 1235, 'Pour the paste into the stock pot and stir constantly until the mixture starts to thicken.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8175, 1235, 'Add the beans, chopped chicken, chili powder, coriander and cumin.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8176, 1235, 'Increase the heat to medium and, stirring frequently, simmer, uncovered for approximately 15-20 minutes or until the mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8177, 1235, 'Reduce the heat to low and add the fresh coriander, single cream and soured cream.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8178, 1235, 'Stir well until the single and soured creams are completely incorporated into the chili.', 15, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8179, 1235, 'Add pepper to taste.', 16, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8180, 1235, 'Serve immediately.', 17, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8181, 1235, 'Garnish with chopped avocado, spring onion, fresh coriander or grated cheese.', 18, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8182, 1235, 'Like most soups, this chili is great refrigerated and served the next day but if you intend on freezing it, leave out the whipping cream and soured cream (they separate when frozen) and add them just before serving.', 19, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8183, 1235, 'If youd like to spice things up a bit, add  -  teaspoon cayenne pepper or red pepper flakes for a slightly hot flavor.', 20, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8184, 1236, 'Combine the chuck, basil, sun-dried tomatoes, onion, garlic, and salt in a large bowl, handling as little as possible. Shape into 2 patties to fit the bun size. Loosely cover with plastic wrap and set aside.For the fennel:Grate 1/2 teaspoons zest from the lemons.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8185, 1236, 'Put the fennel rings in a medium-sized bowl (I used half a fennel bulb) and juice the lemon over half the fennel and toss to coat all the fennel rings.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8186, 1236, 'Add oil and season with salt.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8187, 1236, 'Put the fennel in a grill basket and grill, shaking the basket occasionally, until soft, 10 to 12 minutes. (I did this on the stove top)', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8188, 1236, 'Transfer the fennel to a sheet of foil, sprinkle with the lemon zest, and wrap to keep warm.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8189, 1236, 'Heat a large, heavy nonstick fire-proof skillet on the grill.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8190, 1236, 'Add the bacon and cook until crisp.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8191, 1237, 'Chop vegetables and garlic.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8192, 1237, 'Heat the oven to 400F. On a baking sheet, toss the chopped cauliflower with 1 tablespoon of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8193, 1237, 'Transfer to the oven and roast, tossing once, until florets are browned all over and tender, 20 to 25 minutes.Meanwhile, in a large pot or large saucepan over medium heat, add the bacon, flipping occasionally, until browned and crisp, 6 to 8 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8194, 1237, 'Transfer to paper towels, but reserve the bacon fat in the pot. Once the bacon cools, chop very finely.In the same pot over medium heat, add the anchovies, fennel, leek, and garlic to the bacon fat and cook until the onion and fennel are very soft, 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in the coriander and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8195, 1237, 'Add the roasted cauliflower, broth, bay leaves and 1 cup water. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and cook at a high simmer until the cauliflower is very tender, 10 to 15 minutes.Discard the bay leaves and let cool slightly.In a blender or immersion blender, pure the cauliflower mixture until very smooth.Meanwhile, make the chili oil. Wipe out the pot used to make the cauliflower soup. Over very low heat, add the remaining olive oil, paprika, and chili powder and warm until fragrant, about 1 minute.Ladle the delicious soup into bowls and top with bacon bits and chili oil.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8196, 1238, 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8197, 1238, 'Add in minced garlic, shallots, and green bell pepper.  Stir until fragrant and tender, about 3 minutes. Season it with salt and black pepper.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8198, 1238, 'Add the ground beef to the vegetables. Stir and cook about 5 minutes, until the meat is no longer pink and fully cooked.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8199, 1238, 'Add tomato sauce, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire, and hot sauce into the skillet. Stir to combine. Simmer until thickened.To serve, spoon and pile sloppy meat onto the toasted, buttered bun bottoms and cover with bun tops with your favourite side dish or pickles.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8200, 1239, 'Preheat your oven to 350 degrees F and have a cast iron skillet or oven-safe baking dish ready.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8201, 1239, 'Place the cubed sweet potatoes in a large pot and cover with water. Bring them to a boil over high heat and cook until tender, about 10-15 minutes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8202, 1239, 'Remove from heat and drain.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8203, 1239, 'Transfer to a large bowl and mash.To the bowl with mashed sweet potatoes, stir in 1/2 cup of the melted butter, heavy cream, 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, and the salt until fully incorporated.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8204, 1239, 'Pour the mixture into the cast iron skillet.In a medium bowl, combine the 1/3 cup melted butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, pecans, and bacon. Fold the ingredients together until moist crumbles form.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8205, 1239, 'Sprinkle the mixture on top of the sweet potato mash.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8206, 1239, 'Place the skillet in the oven and bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8207, 1239, 'Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.Enjoy!', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8208, 1240, 'In a large stock pot, bring about 5 cups of water to a boil and cook the parsnips until slightly softened, 5 to 7 minutes.When ready, remove the parsnips with a slotted spoon, but do not drain off the water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8209, 1240, 'Transfer to a bowl. Set aside.Turn heat down to simmer and cover with lid.In the meantime, begin to prepare the other ingredients.While the parsnips are boiling.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8210, 1240, 'Heat a heavy-bottomed saut pan, set over over medium heat.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8211, 1240, 'Add coconut oil.When hot (throw in a piece to see if it sizzles) add the bacon to the oil and thyme and cook, stirring often, about 5 minutes, making sure not to burn the bacon.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8212, 1240, 'Add the red onion, celery and garlic, and cook, stirring often, until the vegetables are translucent, 4 to 5 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8213, 1240, 'Add the carrots and chili paste, stir often, and cook until the carrots soften slightly, 3 to 4 minutes and all the chili paste is blended.Note: This allows the flavor of the chili paste to coat all the ingredients before being diluted by the liquid.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8214, 1240, 'Add the parsnips and transfer most of the parsnip water (or all if you can fit it into your skillet, mine couldnt, I left about a cup in the pot) and stir to combine well.The liquid will turn a light red hue.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8215, 1240, 'Transfer to the simmering pot (with any remaining parsnip water, if some).', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8216, 1240, 'Add the shucked clams and its juice and raise the heat to medium.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8217, 1240, 'Add the coconut milk, non dairy butter spread, and corn to the pot.Bring chowder to a boil.When it comes to a boil, reduce heat to simmer for 5-10 minutes.Ladle individual servings into large soup bowls.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8218, 1240, 'Garnish with parsley (optional).', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:00', '2023-04-25 06:33:00'),
(8219, 1241, 'Scrub the outside of the mussels with a brush.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8220, 1241, 'Remove and discard the beards.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8221, 1241, 'Heat the oil in a wok or large pan add garlic, lemongrass and chili. Cook until slightly brown and fragrant.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8222, 1241, 'Add the mussels to the wok and toss well.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8223, 1241, 'Add in chinese rice wine, water, and Thai basil after about 3 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8224, 1241, 'Mix well.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8225, 1241, 'Put the lid back on for another 1 minutes or so until all the mussels are open (discard any that stay closed).', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8226, 1242, 'Remove skin from salmon fillet and trim away any brown fatty areas.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8227, 1242, 'Place 8 bamboo skewers into the fillet running from the thick side to the thin about 1.5 inches apart. Then slice the fillet so that you have individual pieces of salmon on the skewers.Make a sauce combining the remaining ingredients, including the juice from the lime and the zest. It\'s also easiest to mince the ginger by putting it through a garlic press. You can adjust the mix of ingredients to match your personal tastes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8228, 1242, 'Place the salmon in a deep bowl or ziploc bag and marinate in about half of the sauce, reserving the rest for serving. Refrigerate for 30 minutes to an hour, more will break down the fish and cause it to \"cook\" a bit in the lime juice.Grill skewers on a high heat and serve. Eat with chilled raw Yu Choy, which you use to wrap bits of the fish and drizzle with remaining sauce.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8229, 1243, 'Add fish fillets, egg, fish sauce, corn flour, red curry paste, red chillies and coriander leaves in blender. Blend it until combined and turns in to the thick paste.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8230, 1243, 'Transfer the paste in to a bowl', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8231, 1243, 'Now add spring onion and green beans in to the paste .', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8232, 1243, 'Mix well. Form the paste in to round patties using wet palms. Keep them aside', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8233, 1243, 'Continue Reading Thai Fish Cakes Recipes: http://recipes.sandhira.com/thai-fish-cakes.html', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8234, 1244, 'Cook pasta according to package instructions. During the last minute, add in the broccoli.In the meantime, you can cook the vegetables and prepare the dressing.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8235, 1244, 'Heat olive oil in small non-stick skillet, saut onions until slightly soften.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8236, 1244, 'Add in garlic and continue to saut until fragrant. add in sweet peppers and cook until slightly softened.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8237, 1244, 'Remove from heat, add in remaining ingredients to finish making the sauce.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8238, 1244, 'Add salt and pepper to taste.When the pasta and broccoli is ready, add them to the skillet and stir well. Stir in cilantro leaves.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8239, 1244, 'Served at room temperature or chilled.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8240, 1245, 'Cut the tofu into 1\" cubes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8241, 1245, 'Whisk together sauce ingredients (soy sauce, oyster sauce, fish sauce, brown sugar, and chili paste). Set aside.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8242, 1245, 'Heat 2 tsp sesame oil over medium-high heat in a large wok or pan. When the pan is hot, add the tofu and let cook for 2 minutes on one side, undisturbed, until they develop a crisp crust. Flip and cook 2 minutes more.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8243, 1245, 'Remove the tofu to a plate. Return pan to the heat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8244, 1245, 'Add remaining 1 tsp sesame oil to the pan along with the carrots.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8245, 1245, 'Saute for 3 minutes, until the carrots begin to soften.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8246, 1245, 'Add the bok choy and saute for 2 minutes, until it begins to soften and wilt.Stir in the sauce.Return the tofu to the pan and stir in the corn starch mixture. Allow the sauce to come to a boil for it to thicken. Stir.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8247, 1245, 'Serve with rice.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8248, 1246, 'Pound all the ingredients in a clay mortar using a wooden pestle, then add carrot and mangoes.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8249, 1246, 'Serve chilled with roasted coarse peanuts.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8250, 1247, 'Prepare marinade.Slice beef.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8251, 1247, 'Add beef and marinade to freezer bag. Marinate for 2-4 in the fridge. The longer the better.Slice/chop all your veggies.Prepare your curry paste.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8252, 1247, 'Add oil to wok and heat.Cook beef until done, approximately 10 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8253, 1247, 'Remove from wok and set aside.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8254, 1247, 'Add onions and cook for about 2 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8255, 1247, 'Add carrots, peppers and mushrooms.When almost done (to your preferred tenderness) add snap peas and bok choy. Cook about 2 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8256, 1247, 'Remove veggies from wok and set aside.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8257, 1247, 'Add curry paste to wok and heat through.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8258, 1247, 'Add coconut milk and whisk until smooth.Bring to a boil.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8259, 1247, 'Add beef to the sauce.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8260, 1247, 'Add veggies to the beef/sauce mixture.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8261, 1247, 'Heat through.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8262, 1247, 'Serve over your choice of noodles or riice.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8263, 1248, 'Julianne the green mango and diced the tomato', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8264, 1248, 'Mix and place in the bowl Roughly pound chilli and garlic and add the fish sauce Season with sugar to balance the taste', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8265, 1248, 'Add lime juice for the final touch', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8266, 1248, 'Pour the dressing in bowl of mix green mango and tomato, fold gently', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8267, 1248, 'Place on the bed of your favourite lettuce and serve', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8268, 1249, 'In a small bowl, combine the dressing ingredients and stir until the sugar has dissolved. Taste and adjust with more sugar or fish sauce if needed (some limes are more tart than others). Set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8269, 1249, 'Slice the sausage thinly on the diagonal.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8270, 1249, 'Place in a non stick skillet over medium heat and saut until the edges are slightly browned and sausage is cooked thru, about 5 minutes. Dont over cook. Set aside to cool', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8271, 1249, 'Peel the cucumbers, slice thinly and place in a large bowl. Thinly slice the green onions on the diagonal and add to the bowl.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8272, 1249, 'Add the bean sprouts, cooked sausage and the dressing. Lightly toss and serve on plates with jasmine rice on the same plate.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8273, 1249, 'Garnish with a few slivers of sliced hot chili pepper, if desired, and a few leaves of fresh parsley or cilantro.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8274, 1249, 'Serves 2 as a main course salad.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8275, 1250, 'Toss faux chicken strips with shoyu and oil until well coated.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8276, 1250, 'Heat in saute pan over medium-low heat until heated through.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8277, 1250, 'In medium bowl, add sesame seeds, sprouts, slaw mix, basil, sugar, vinegar and salt & pepper. Toss until thoroughly coated. Set aside.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8278, 1250, 'To make the SAUCE: in small bowl, whisk Earth Balance natural peanut butter with shoyu and vinegar.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8279, 1250, 'Add in oil while whisking until consistency is slightly runny.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8280, 1250, 'Chop off the rough end of romaine leaves; smooth out flat and pile on the faux chicken, slaw mixture and drizzle with peanut sauce.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8281, 1250, 'Top with crushed peanuts (optional) and carefully wrap and roll, starting from one end. Leave seam side down.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8282, 1251, 'Prepare the sauce in a small bowl by mixing the fish sauce, lime juice and sugar. Set this aside.Finely chop the shallots and cut the spring onion stalks. While a pan is set on medium fire add coconut oil to the pan and then the shallots.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8283, 1251, 'Add the ground pork and cook, making sure to break it up into bits &amp; pieces.When its 90% cooked, add the sauce mixture and let it simmer.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8284, 1251, 'Add the chili flakes.At the last moment, you want to add the spring onions and handful of cilantro (I like to tear it up with my fingers over the pan). Finally add fresh mint leaves to garnish.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8285, 1251, 'Serve on a bed of crisp lettuce to eat as lettuce wraps.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8286, 1252, 'Chop all ingredients &quot;mise en place.&quot;', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8287, 1252, 'Grab a bowl and combine the shallots, fish sauce, hot peppers, sugar, lime juice, and half of the scallions, mint, and cilantro.  You’re nearly halfway done :)', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8288, 1252, 'Heat 1 Tbsp neutral oil (link Pantry one) over medium heat and cook the ground pork for about 5 minutes.  This step is not meant to brown the ground pork, but just to cook it until it’s no longer pink.  I use a wooden spoon and move the meat around frequently to achieve even cooking and break up any clumps.  ', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8289, 1252, 'Remove the pork and drain the juices (in other words, use a slotted spoon to take the meat out of the skillet).', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8290, 1252, 'Let the meat cool a couple minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8291, 1252, 'Combine the meat with the sauce and give it good stir.  Taste it.  Now is a good time to add some Maldon salt to brighten up the flavors a bit.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8292, 1252, 'Serve over cooked rice, top with remaining scallions, mint, and cilantro, and serve with an ice cold beer (a Corona Extra works excellent).', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8293, 1253, 'On medium flame, fry the garlic until fragrant and not brown.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8294, 1253, 'Add in the chicken and cook until nearly done. Then, add in Thai chili paste and stir well.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8295, 1253, 'Add a bit less than recommended if you cant take spiciness.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8296, 1253, 'Add in the onion, cashew nuts, dry chilies and spring onion. Give it a good mix and cook for  about 2 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8297, 1253, 'Then, season with soya sauce.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8298, 1253, 'Add in dark soya sauce to sweeten the dish and give it a little bit of colour.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8299, 1253, 'Serve warm.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8300, 1254, 'Peel and devein shrimp. Wash, dry and steam basil, mince garlic, thinly slice seeded chilies, mince white part of onion and cut green part into 1 inch pieces. Recipe can be prepared ahead to this stage.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8301, 1254, 'Heat wok over high heat. Swirl oil into wok and heat almost to smoking.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8302, 1254, 'Add garlic, chilies, onions (white part), and cook 10-15 seconds; add shrimp and stir fry 20 seconds or until they change color.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8303, 1254, 'Add fish sauce, soy sauce, sugar, chicken, stock and green part of onions and bring mixture to a boil. Stir in basil and cook 20 seconds or until leaves wilt and shrimp are firm and pink. Dish is supposed to be soupy.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8304, 1254, 'Serve over hot cooked rice.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8305, 1255, 'Heat a large cast iron skillet over medium heat. Once hot, dry-fry (meaning, dont add any fat or oil to the pan) the whole chilies for one minute, then set aside in a small bowl. They should be fragrant and slightly darker in color, but not burnt. In the same pan, dry-fry the chopped onion, bell pepper, and garlic for 2 minutes until brown but not burnt, then set aside on a large plate.Toss in the tomatoes and dry-fry for 1-2 minutes until charred on the outside, stirring frequently. Set on the plate with the onions, pepper, and garlic. Turn the stove off, then use your hands to break apart the chilies into smaller pieces. Dont try to use a knife, because they will fly all over the kitchen.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8306, 1255, 'Place the chilies in the bowl of a blender or large food processor, then wash your hands thoroughly with soap and warm water to remove any oils left from the chilies.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:23', '2023-04-25 06:33:23'),
(8307, 1255, 'Add the third cup fish sauce, quarter cup lime juice, and sugar to the blender, along with the reserved onion, bell pepper, garlic, and tomatoes. Pulse on chop mode or equivalent until the mixture forms a chunky sauce.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8308, 1255, 'Serve either warm or chilled.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8309, 1256, 'In the heated oil, fry curry paste till aromatic and oil splits.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8310, 1256, 'Add bay leaves and lamb.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8311, 1256, 'Pour 1/2 liter of water (more if you like)', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8312, 1256, 'Stir and simmer till lamb is half cooked.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8313, 1256, 'Add potatoes and season with salt.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8314, 1256, 'Continue to simmer till potatoes and lamb are tender and soft.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8315, 1256, 'Pour in fish sauce, lime juice and coconut milk.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8316, 1256, 'Gently stir and remove from heat.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8317, 1257, 'Blend all the dressing ingredients together.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8318, 1257, 'Mix in all of the chopped vegetables, herb, and peanuts (if you want the peanuts).', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8319, 1257, 'Add more of any of the flavors that you prefer, which is the true Thai way.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8320, 1257, 'Garnish each plate with cilantro leaves and sliced limes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8321, 1257, 'Serve with a patter of add-ins:Lime slices, red pepper flakes, chopped cilantro, chopped peanuts, Thai sweet chili sauce, sugar, salt, etc. for your guests to add more of their favorite flavors.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8322, 1258, 'Combine the first four ingredient in a medium sauce pan.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8323, 1258, 'Heat mixture until it boils. Boils for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8324, 1258, 'Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8325, 1258, 'Add the Nuggets last. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper or foil. Cookies will harden as they cool. Makes 24 cookies', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8326, 1259, 'Remove the leafy parts of the beetroot. Do not trim the roots so that it does not bleed', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8327, 1259, 'Add the beetroot to a pot, cover with plenty of water, bring to the boil and then simmer until tender (between 45-60 mins depending on its size).', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8328, 1259, 'Drain the beetroot and when pieces are cool down peel and chop them.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8329, 1259, 'Add the oil to a saucepan and fry the onion for about 7 mins until soft.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8330, 1259, 'Add in the beetroot and curry paste and cook for a few mins.Stir in the coconut milk and stock, season with salt and pepper and bring to the boil then reduce to a simmer for about 5 mins.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8331, 1259, 'Let the soup cool and whizz with a hand held blender or in a food processor.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8332, 1259, 'Add lemon juice to you taste and adjust season and serve.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8333, 1260, 'Heat the coconut milk in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring constantly to avoid curdling.Bring to a low simmer, then add the sugar and salt and whisk together until combined.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8334, 1260, 'Remove from heat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8335, 1260, 'Pour about 3/4 of the sweetened coconut milk onto the warm rice.Allow to sit for about 10 minutes or until the rice has completely absorbed the coconut milk.In the meantime, carefully peel and chop the mango into 1/2\" pieces.Assemble your dessert shots by putting about 1 tablespoon of sweetened sticky rice into each shot glass.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8336, 1260, 'Layer a generous amount of mango chunks on top, then add more sticky rice.Top each shot with a small amount of the remaining coconut milk.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8337, 1260, 'Garnish with a couple extra pieces of mango and a basil or mint leaf, and enjoy!', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8338, 1261, 'Simply mix ingredients together in a bowl and stir until well combined.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8339, 1262, 'For satay:Method:Marinate chicken with marinade for at least 2 hours or preferably overnight in the fridge.Make sure to soak bamboo sticks in water for 30 minutes before skewering the meat.Cook satays on greased grill griddle and brush on oil and leftover marinade as needed. Cook about 3 minutes on each side.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8340, 1262, 'Serve satays with peanut sauce, cucumber and onions.For Peanut Sauce:Method:Bring coconut milk to a boil and add the rest of the ingredients and adjust to taste accordingly.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8341, 1263, 'Spray a foil-lined baking sheet with nonstick spray.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8342, 1263, 'Place fish on baking sheet.Mince green onions, basil, ginger, and garlic.Rub mixture on both sides of the fish.Season with salt, pepper, and cayenne.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8343, 1263, 'Brush with sesame oil.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8344, 1263, 'Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes, or cover and refrigerate for up to 2 hours.Preheat oven to 450F.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8345, 1263, 'Bake fish uncovered for 10-12 minutes, until golden.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8346, 1264, 'Rough chop cucumbers.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8347, 1264, 'In a medium, securely sealable container, combine soy sauce, rice vinegar, and sesame oil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8348, 1264, 'Add cucumbers to the marinade, close container and shake.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8349, 1264, 'Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours. Shake cucumbers periodically, or leave overnight to marinate. Note, the longer the cucumbers are left in the marinade the saltier they become. I\'ve left them in the marinade for up to 3 days and the cucumbers were good.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8350, 1264, 'Serve and enjoy!', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8351, 1265, 'Peanut Chili Vinaigrette', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8352, 1265, 'Mince ginger and garlic.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8353, 1265, 'Mix all ingredients well and let mingle in the fridge for at least 30 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8354, 1265, 'Panera Spicy Thai Salad', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8355, 1265, 'If you’re using a rotisserie chicken, there’s no cooking involved (except for microwaving the edamame (if used). If you prefer to use chicken breasts, make sure it stays juicy after cooking.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8356, 1265, 'Grab a large plate – I prefer a bowl-shaped pasta plate. Start by placing the chopped romaine on the plate.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8357, 1265, 'Add carrots and bell peppers, followed by the edamame, wonton strips, and slivered almonds.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8358, 1265, 'Top with sliced chicken meat, drizzle the sauce over, and top it off with some roughly chopped cilantro.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8359, 1265, 'Enjoy!', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8360, 1266, 'Heat 2 tbsp oil and saut chopped garlic until fragrant.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8361, 1266, 'Add in asparagus, stir fry a while then add in carrot and stir well.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8362, 1266, 'Add in fish sauce, sugar and a little water if it becomes too dry.Now add in squid, stir-fry for about 1-2 minutes, or until squid curls up. Don\'t overcook squid, as it will become rubbery.Test for taste, adding more fish sauce if not salty enough. But if too salty for your taste, add a little more sugar. Dish up and serve immediately.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:24', '2023-04-25 06:33:24'),
(8363, 1267, 'Soak the quartered cabbage in the brine solution for 4 hours, weighing the cabbage down with a heavy plate.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8364, 1267, 'Remove and drain.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8365, 1267, 'Place garlic cloves, rice, fermented shrimp, fish sauce, sugar, chilly paste and chilly flakes in a food processor and zap to a smooth paste. Stir in spring onions.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8366, 1267, 'Stuff the cabbage with the paste, making sure to stuff in between the individual leaves and coating every inch of it.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8367, 1267, 'Place kimchi into an airtight container and leave at room temperature for a day before leaving it to ferment further in the fridge for at least another week before consuming. I left mine for about 3 weeks.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8368, 1268, 'Cook noodles according to package directions', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8369, 1268, 'In a large pan or wok over medium heat, heat olive oil and 1 Tbsp sesame oil', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8370, 1268, 'Add onion slices and garlic and saut for about 1 min', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8371, 1268, 'Add rest of vegetables and cook for 4-5 min, until the vegetables are half-cooked and still a bit crispy', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8372, 1268, 'Turn heat to low and add cooked noodles, soy sauce, sugar, and the remaining sesame oil', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8373, 1268, 'Mix to combine and cook for another 2 min', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8374, 1268, 'Add salt or more soy sauce if needed (or if you want it a bit sweeter, add a touch more sugar)', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8375, 1268, 'If using sesame seeds, add them at finish', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8376, 1269, 'Shred cabbage in 2 inch strips.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8377, 1269, 'Mix with half the salt.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8378, 1269, 'Let stand 30 minutes. Wash and drain.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8379, 1269, 'Mix the scallions, garlic, ginger, chili pepper, cabbage and the rest of salt. Pack into a crock or glass jar.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8380, 1269, 'Put the containers aside for three or four days in a cool location. After that, store it in the refrigerator.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8381, 1270, 'Remove discolored, bruised outer leaves of cabbage and rinse well under cold water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8382, 1270, 'Cut cabbage head into desired pieces; smaller 2-inch pieces is recommended for easier access later.  In 3 separate large bowls, prepare one cup sea salt and water mixture for each bowl.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8383, 1270, 'Sprinkle remaining 1 cup of sea salt onto the leaves of the cabbages before soaking them in the salt water. Cabbages should be partially submerged in the salt water.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8384, 1270, 'Let sit for a minimum 6 hours but 12 hours is preferred.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8385, 1270, 'Once finished soaking, rinse the cabbage leaves thoroughly under cold water several times.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8386, 1270, 'Remove water from the cabbage by giving them a squeeze (they should have a rubbery texture by now) to remove excess water. Set in a colander or basket for at least 2 hours so the water will drain out thoroughly. Meanwhile, prepare the red pepper mixture to be mixed with cabbage leaves.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8387, 1270, 'Prepare 3 tbsp of the sweet rice flour with 3 cups of water into a small pot. Bring to a boil and whisk until the mixture turns into a glue-like consistency.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8388, 1270, 'Let cool and set aside.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8389, 1270, 'In a food processor, puree onion, garlic, ginger and some water until smooth.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8390, 1270, 'Pour gochugaru (chili flakes) in a large mixing bowl, add the garlic mixture puree, cooled rice glue, fish sauce, salted shrimp, sugar, and sesame seeds.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8391, 1270, 'Mix well and add the sliced radish and green onions.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8392, 1270, 'Lather each cabbage piece with red pepper mixture by rubbing them well (rubber gloves highly recommended). Continue until all the cabbage leaves are covered in the red pepper mixture. Pack them inside air-tight glass jars/containers.  Set out at room temperature for 2 days for fermentation to take place. After that, place in the refrigerator and serve as needed. The kimchi may keep for 2 or 3 months in the refrigerator.*Making kimchi is not easy, but if done right, the rewards are endless. You can take the easy way out and purchase them at your local Korean grocery store and even possibly in the Asian foods section of your local grocery.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8393, 1271, 'Cook rice according to package directions.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8394, 1271, 'Cut vegetables into matchstick pieces and set aside for sauteing.3.In a large non-stick pan/skillet, bring 2 cups water to a boil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(8395, 1271, 'Add spinach and cook, stirring constantly until wilted; drain. When cool enough to handle, squeeze spinach dry into a ball.4.Wipe out skillet; heat 1 tsp olive oil over medium-high.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8396, 1271, 'Add carrots and cook until soft, 3 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8397, 1271, 'Add garlic and cook until fragrant or semi-browned, 1 minute.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8398, 1271, 'Add cucumber slices mixed with gochugaru (red pepper flakes).', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8399, 1271, 'Combine spinach and soy sauce; set aside until serving.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8400, 1271, 'Add thinly sliced beef to non-stick pan and heat until browned. Wipe down with napkin.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8401, 1271, 'Heat 1 tsp olive oil in non-stick pan over medium-high.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8402, 1271, 'Add eggs and cook until whites are set and yolks are still runny, about 5 minutes.7.Divide rice among four bowls; top with vegetables and eggs.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8403, 1271, 'Drizzle each with sesame oil, sprinkle with sesame seeds. Top with gochujang (red pepper paste) or Sriracha sauce as substitute.*Bibimbab and its main ingredients (usually rice and vegetables) can be chosen at one\'s preference. This is the main reason why bibimbab is so appealing; it suits vegetarians, dieters, health-conscience eaters, and even meat-lovers, who are more than welcome to add beef to their liking. For us, since we usually have rice available to eat at all times, we simply slice up any available vegetables or lettuce leaf varieties in the fridge for an \"instant\" and very satisfying bibimbab meal. So feel free to deviate from the original recipe!', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8404, 1272, 'Optional step: Precook the onions and garlic in some olive oil until caramelized. This will add some depth and flavor to the patties.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8405, 1272, 'Place the ground pork in a large bowl along with the first six ingredients on the list.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8406, 1272, 'Mix well with your hands and then form into round patties. Overnight marinating is optional.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8407, 1272, 'In a frying pan or cast iron skillet, lightly coated with olive oil or butter and cook the patties on medium high heat, roughly 4 minutes on each side. Cook eggs accordingly after finishing the patties.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8408, 1272, 'With the remaining bits from the meat, add in the minced garlic and halved cherry tomatoes, saute for a few minutes until browned. Scrape off meat pieces in the process.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8409, 1272, 'Add remaining sauce ingredients and cook until it reduces, about 5 minutes. Tomato skins will peel off (discard if necessary).', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8410, 1272, 'Add flour to thicken the sauce and adjust taste as needed.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8411, 1273, 'Cook rice according to package directions.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8412, 1273, 'Cut vegetables into matchstick pieces and set aside for sauteing.3.In a large non-stick pan/skillet, bring 2 cups water to a boil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8413, 1273, 'Add spinach and cook, stirring constantly until wilted; drain. When cool enough to handle, squeeze spinach dry into a ball.4.Wipe out skillet; heat 1 tsp olive oil over medium-high.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8414, 1273, 'Add carrots and cook until soft, 3 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8415, 1273, 'Add garlic and cook until fragrant or semi-browned, 1 minute.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8416, 1273, 'Add cucumber slices mixed with gochugaru (red pepper flakes).', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8417, 1273, 'Combine spinach and soy sauce; set aside until serving.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8418, 1273, 'Add thinly sliced beef to non-stick pan and heat until browned. Wipe down with napkin.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8419, 1273, 'Heat 1 tsp olive oil in non-stick pan over medium-high.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8420, 1273, 'Add eggs and cook until whites are set and yolks are still runny, about 5 minutes.7.Divide rice among four bowls; top with vegetables and eggs.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8421, 1273, 'Drizzle each with sesame oil, sprinkle with sesame seeds. Top with gochujang (red pepper paste) or Sriracha sauce as substitute.*Bibimbab and its main ingredients (usually rice and vegetables) can be chosen at one\'s preference. This is the main reason why bibimbab is so appealing; it suits vegetarians, dieters, health-conscience eaters, and even meat-lovers, who are more than welcome to add beef to their liking. For us, since we usually have rice available to eat at all times, we simply slice up any available vegetables or lettuce leaf varieties in the fridge for an \"instant\" and very satisfying bibimbab meal. So feel free to deviate from the original recipe!', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8422, 1274, 'In a large pot over medium heat, warm the coconut oil until melted.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8423, 1274, 'Add the onion and cook until translucent, 4 to 6 minutes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8424, 1274, 'Add the ground pork and cook, breaking it up with a spoon, until browned, 8 to 10 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8425, 1274, 'Add the garlic and ginger and cook for another minute.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8426, 1274, 'Add the cabbage. Then stir in the soy sauce, fish sauce, sesame oil and kimchi and kimchi juice.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8427, 1274, 'Add the bone broth and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer and cook, covered, until the cabbage is completely soft, 15 to 20 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8428, 1274, 'Remove from the heat and garnish with the scallions.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8429, 1275, 'Trim off fat from pork chops (usually on the sides), then pound into thin pieces with tenderizer. Season with salt and pepper.Coat pork with flour, then beaten egg, and lastly panko bread crumbs.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8430, 1275, 'Heat vegetable oil in pan or skillet on medium heat.Fry until golden brown and cooked through (you can cut to check insides). Usually takes about 8-10 minutes total if fully submerged in oil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8431, 1275, 'Remove cutlets from the oil and drain on paper towel to remove excess oil and cool.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8432, 1275, 'Drain shredded cabbage well.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8433, 1275, 'Cut each cutlet into small pieces and serve on plate with cabbage slaw.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8434, 1275, 'Serve with katsu sauce for dipping and serve with rice.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8435, 1276, 'Rinse beef, pat dry, and cut across the grain into 1/8-inch-thick slices about 3 inches long. In a small bowl, mix beef with 1/4 cup Korean Marinade.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8436, 1276, 'Remove and discard bean stem ends and strings.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8437, 1276, 'Cut beans diagonally in 3-inch lengths.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8438, 1276, 'Cut carrot into matchstick-size pieces about 3 inches long.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8439, 1276, 'In a 14-inch wok or 12-inch frying pan over high heat, mix 1/2 cup water, beans, and carrot. Cover and stir occasionally just until tender to bite, about 3 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8440, 1276, 'Drain; immerse in cold water.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8441, 1276, 'Drain when cool. In a bowl, mix with vinegar, sesame oil, sugar, and salt to taste.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8442, 1276, 'Place wok over high heat; when hot, add salad oil.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8443, 1276, 'Add beef with liquid in bowl; stir until meat is no longer pink, about 2 minutes.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8444, 1276, 'Add remaining marinade and broth to pan; stir until boiling.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8445, 1276, 'Scoop rice into bowls; add beef and sauce, then vegetables and seasonings.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8446, 1276, 'Sprinkle with onions and sesame seed.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8447, 1276, 'This recipe yields 4 servings.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8448, 1276, 'Comments: If you can\'t find toasted sesame seed, stir regular sesame seed in a frying pan over low heat until golden, 1 minute.', 14, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8449, 1277, 'In a pan, pour about two inches of oil and heat on medium heat till hot.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8450, 1277, 'Cut chicken on the diagonal into thick strips, about two inches wide.In a bowl, beat eggs.In another container, place flour.Coat chicken strips in egg mixture first, then generously pat with flour, covering all sides. I will often give it a couple of coatings. There should be a thick layer of batter on the chicken pieces.When oil is hot, fry chicken pieces till golden brown, about 3 minutes on each side.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8451, 1277, 'Remove chicken, and let rest on a paper towel to drain the oil.To make candy sauce, place soy sauce and sugar in a bowl and mix together, about 30 seconds.The sugar will not completely dissolve, but the mixture should be thick, and not grainy.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8452, 1277, 'Add sesame seeds and mix to incorporate.Dip chicken in sauce,  covering all sides.Repeat, till all pieces are covered.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8453, 1277, 'Serve with rice, drizzle remain sauce over chicken.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8454, 1277, 'Garnish with sliced scallions.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8455, 1278, 'Mix the marinade ingredients (brown sugar, soy sauce, ginger, sesame oil, chili garlic sauce, and ginger).', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8456, 1278, 'Pour over your sliced pork.Marinate no less then 4 hours; overnight is recommended.Preheat your grill to high.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8457, 1278, 'Place pork on grill and grill each side 3 minutes or until cooked through.If you want a sauce to pour over your meat, boil your leftover marinade in a sauce pan for a few minutes until it boils down and thickens. You can then add rice vinegar to taste to thin it and decrease the sweetness.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8458, 1278, 'Pour sauce over meat.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8459, 1279, 'Mix first 6 ingredients', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8460, 1279, 'Put chicken and vegetables in heavy bottom pot', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8461, 1279, 'Add sauce, stir', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8462, 1279, 'Pour in some water, bring to a boil. Cover and leave on medium heat about 30 min', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8463, 1279, 'Sprinkle with cilantro or spring onion and enjoy!', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8464, 1280, 'Soak the ribs in a bowl of cold water for about an hour to drain the blood, changing the water if necessary.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8465, 1280, 'Mix sliced radish and add with the seasoning sauce.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8466, 1280, 'After soaking and rinsing the ribs, place in a large pot and cover with water until submerged.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8467, 1280, 'Add half onion, few garlic pieces, and a slice of ginger (this step is optional).', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8468, 1280, 'Bring to a boil for about 15 minutes, removing any foam or scum that float to the top.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8469, 1280, 'Drain and rinse the ribs under cold water removing any impurities.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8470, 1280, 'Add new water just until ribs are submerged (more water can be added if desired).', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8471, 1280, 'Bring to a boil, and then simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8472, 1280, 'Add the radish and sauce mixture and cook for an additional 10 minutes.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8473, 1280, 'Lastly, add the vermicelli noodles and scallions and cook for another few minutes.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8474, 1280, 'Garnish with thinly cut egg strips and toasted sesame seeds.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8475, 1280, 'Serve with rice and other banchan (side dishes).', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8476, 1281, 'Put all the ingredients into a food processor and blend everything until it is a smooth paste.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8477, 1281, 'Toss it in a bowl with some freshly cooked pasta of your choice and serve, garnishing with some leftover pine nuts.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8478, 1282, 'Peel off thigh skins with a paring knife. Trim off excess fat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8479, 1282, 'Cut into one single \"steak\" piece working around the bone. Save smaller pieces for cooking as well. Set aside in a large mixing bowl.Pulse the marinade ingredients in a food processor until smooth.Coat the chicken pieces with the marinade. Marinate overnight in the refrigerator or a minimum of 6-12 hours. With a skewer or toothpick, piercing the thighs for extra marinade absorption is optional.Preheat a skillet or non stick pan over medium heat.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8480, 1282, 'Add the chicken thighs and cook for about 15-20 minutes or until cooked through. To ensure fully cooked thighs, use a meat thermometer and check for a reading of 165-170F.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8481, 1282, 'Transfer to a serving plate and garnish with scallion.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8482, 1282, 'Serve with lettuce leaves. Enjoy!', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8483, 1283, 'Set a large skillet over medium high heat.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8484, 1283, 'When hot add coconut oil.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8485, 1283, 'Add onions, let it sit for a minute or two to brown, then stir occasionally.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8486, 1283, 'When translucent add the garlic, stir to combine for another minute.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8487, 1283, 'Add grated sweet potato, let it sit for 2 minutes before stirring to get some caramelization. (I grated in food processor, then hand sliced any large pieces that didnt go through the grater).', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8488, 1283, 'Season with kosher salt and pepper.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8489, 1283, 'Add coconut nectar. Stir often.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8490, 1283, 'Cook down for about 5 minutes.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8491, 1283, 'You will see some bits stuck on the bottom of the pan that look burned, thats fine and will be de-glazed.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8492, 1283, 'Add sherry vinegar then scrape any charred bits on the bottom of the pan to deglaze.', 10, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8493, 1283, 'Add chopped kimchi, stir to combine well, about a minute.', 11, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8494, 1283, 'Turn off heat.', 12, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8495, 1283, 'Add remaining chives for garnish.', 13, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8496, 1284, 'Wash the potatoes then peel and rinse in cold water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8497, 1284, 'Cut into about 1 inch by 1 inch cubes (2.5 cm squared) and rinse again.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8498, 1284, 'Bring a large pot of water to a full boil, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and the cubed potatoes', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8499, 1284, 'Boil until semi tender (Korean chop stick or fork passes through with slight resistance). This will take 8-15 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8500, 1284, 'Drain and let cool after youve sprinkled them with your white pepper.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8501, 1284, 'While the potatoes are cooking, clean the apples and Korean pear, then cut into about 1/2 inch by 1/2 inch pieces (1.25 cm squared) and add to bowl. Toss until well mixed.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8502, 1284, 'In a medium mixing bowl combine the mayonnaise, pepper and sugar (optional) then mix well.', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8503, 1284, 'Add dressing to potato mix and stir until well mixed.  If desired garnish with toasted sesame seed.', 8, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8504, 1284, 'Chill and serve cold or at room temperature.', 9, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8505, 1285, 'Line a 23cm round pan (with removable base) set aside.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8506, 1285, 'Combine crushed digestive biscuit crumbs and melted butter together in a mixing bowl.Press the biscuit crumbs onto the base of the prepared pan and put it in the refrigerator for later use.Measure water into a bowl and sprinkle in the gelatin (without stirring with a spoon). Set aside to allow the gelatin to swell (few mins) before setting the bowl over a pot of simmering hot water. Stir with a spoon and once  the gelatin melts, remove the bowl from the pot and set aside to cool to room temperature.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8507, 1285, 'Whisk non-dairy topping cream until peak form (not too stiff), set aside.In another mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth, then gradually add in milk until combined.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8508, 1285, 'Add lemon juice, honey citron tea paste, mix to combine and add gelatin solution, mix well.Fold in whipped non-dairy topping cream, with a hand whisk.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8509, 1285, 'Pour cream cheese mixture on the prepared cake tin and refrigerate for at least 4 hours until set.To make the topping, heat the gelatin (method same as above) and stir in honey citron tea paste, mix well and leave to cool.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8510, 1285, 'Spread the honey citron tea paste thinly and evenly on top of the cheesecake.Refrigerate the cheese cake until it is ready to serve.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8511, 1286, 'Wash each perilla leaf individually through running water and shake off excess water.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8512, 1286, 'Place in a colander until dried; set aside for at least 15 minutes.2.In a mixing bowl, combine all the other ingredients together with the finely chopped onion, green onion, and minced garlic. In a tupperware or plastic container, place a spoonful of the sauce on the bottom.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8513, 1286, 'Add one perilla leaf then put another spoonful of the sauce to coat the leaf. Continue alternating the layers with a perilla leaf and the sauce until stacks are formed side by side.3.Continue lathering the leaves one at a time until each one is covered with the sauce. If you run out of sauce, it will collect at the bottom of the tupperware. Reuse any runoff sauce to complete the process4.Store in the refrigerator for at least a few days. When ready, serve as a side dish (banchan) with the main dish.*This particular side dish (along with regular gim, seaweed) is perfect with a bowl of rice. Many Koreans (with chopsticks in hand) simply wrap a single leaf around some rice and indulge in its deliciousness. The salty and sour perilla leaves with the sticky rice really go great together.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8514, 1287, 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat and brown hamburger with garlic in the sesame oil.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8515, 1287, 'Drain most of the fat and add brown sugar, soy sauce, ginger, salt, pepper, and red peppers.  Simmer for a few minutes to blend the flavors.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8516, 1287, 'Serve over steamed rice and top with green onions', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8517, 1288, 'Be sure to soak sweet rice in a large bowl of water (partially submerged) at least an hour before usage. There should be directions to usage so check the package if available.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8518, 1288, 'Fill a large pot with about 8 cups of water, boil and then add whole chicken breasts, garlic cloves, and about 1 tbsp of salt. Boil on medium-high setting for about 20 minutes.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8519, 1288, 'Remove chicken pieces from the heat and rinse under running cold water to cool. The chicken pieces can be torn into strips by hands or cut into thinly diced pieces according to preference.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8520, 1288, 'As for the chicken broth, strain through a sieve and/or remove the garlic cloves with a spoon (saving is optional). Reserve chicken broth and pour about 3-4 cups of broth back into the pot.', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8521, 1288, 'Drain the water from the sweet rice and combine with shredded chicken and diced vegetables into the pot. Cook for about 20 minutes on medium heat, stirring frequently to prevent rice from sticking on the bottom. Keep the lid partially covered until a thick consistency is achieved.', 5, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8522, 1288, 'Add more chicken broth or water if necessary.', 6, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8523, 1288, 'Plate into soup bowls while topping with a dash of sesame oil, soy sauce and green onion slices according to taste. Enjoy!', 7, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8524, 1289, 'Prepare the vegetables by thinly slicing them into 2-inch strips. This allows them to be eaten comfortably with the noodles. Shred the lettuce into desired pieces and lay them as a bed for the noodles.', 1, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8525, 1289, 'Boil the noodles in pot for about 7 minutes or shortly after the noodles separate on their own. It\'s best to have slightly undercooked noodles as opposed to overcooked noodles, as they will continue to soften as you eat them. For extra spiciness, add in 1 tbsp of gochujang (red pepper paste) to the original sauce packets.', 2, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8526, 1289, 'After draining the noodles under cold water for several minutes, top on the bed of lettuce and top with pre-cut vegetables and garnish with sesame seeds and alfalfa sprouts.', 3, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8527, 1289, 'Add the spicy sauce according to taste preference. Enjoy!', 4, '2023-04-25 06:33:31', '2023-04-25 06:33:31'),
(8528, 1291, 'Cook the pasta according to package instructions.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:00:15', '2023-04-26 07:00:15'),
(8529, 1291, 'While the pasta is cooking, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:00:15', '2023-04-26 07:00:15'),
(8530, 1291, 'Add the tomatoes and garlic to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.', 3, '2023-04-26 07:00:15', '2023-04-26 07:00:15'),
(8531, 1291, 'Add the cooked pasta and basil to the skillet and toss to combine.', 4, '2023-04-26 07:00:15', '2023-04-26 07:00:15'),
(8532, 1292, 'Cook Italian sausage in a medium skillet until browned.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8533, 1292, 'Drain on paper towels and crumble into small pieces.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8534, 1292, 'Heat oven to 450 degrees.', 3, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8535, 1292, 'Place parchment paper on a baking pan and lightly flour.', 4, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8536, 1292, 'Roll dough out to form a large rectangle.', 5, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8537, 1292, 'Brush a thin layer of pizza sauce on dough.', 6, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8538, 1292, 'Layer on crumbled sausage then mozzarella cheese.', 7, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8539, 1292, 'Place pepperoni slices on top of cheese then sprinkle with 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.Gently roll in short sides of dough to form a seal around filling.Starting on long side of dough, carefully roll into one third of Stromboli. Using parchment, roll dough again until reaching opposite end. Pinch together and place seam side down.', 8, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8540, 1292, 'Mix egg with 1 tablespoon of water.', 9, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8541, 1292, 'Brush egg mixture over Stromboli and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 Parmesan cheese.', 10, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8542, 1292, 'Place in oven and IMMEDIATELY TURN OVEN DOWN to 350 degrees.', 11, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8543, 1292, 'Bake for approximately 18 minutes.', 12, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8544, 1292, 'Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes. Test center of turnover. If dough is not completely cooked, slice Stromboli in half and bake for additional 5-8 minutes.', 13, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8545, 1292, 'Serve with warm pizza sauce', 14, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8546, 1293, 'Take a package of OREO cookies and crush them up finely.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8547, 1293, 'Take softened cream cheese and mix well with cookie crumbs.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8548, 1293, 'Roll into one inch cookie balls, and then freeze for 10 minutes.', 3, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8549, 1293, 'Dip cookie balls into melted chocolate and place on a prepared cookie sheet covered with wax paper.', 4, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8550, 1293, 'Place into the refrigerator for 15 minutes to an hour before decorating.', 5, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8551, 1293, 'Add 5 candy corn to the back of the ball as tail feathers.', 6, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8552, 1293, 'Use icing as glue to attach the candy eyes.', 7, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8553, 1293, 'Cut one candy corn into pieces, using the white tip as the nose, and the orange part (cut in half) as feet.', 8, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8554, 1294, 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Melt the butter and add the celeryand onion to a medium pot and saute over medium heat for about 8 minutes.Step 2: Stir in 2/3 cup flour, salt and pepper, celery seed, onion powder, garlic powder, and Italian seasoning. Slowly whisk in the chicken broth and milk, stirring constantly until the the mixture begins to thicken and then simmer lightly until thickened.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8555, 1294, 'Remove from heat and mix with the drained vegetables and turkey.Step 3: Fill two pie crusts with your turkey and vegetable mixture. Carefully top each pie with another pie crust, pinching the sides together.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8556, 1295, 'Yes, these are called SPICY hot wings for a reason. I like adding the brown sugar to give them a little sweeter taste, but it is by far a delicious spicy recipe more than anything.To get started, mix the brown sugar, crushed garlic, hot sauce, and cayenne pepper into a medium mixing bowl.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8557, 1295, 'Mix well and then set aside.Take the cooking spray and spray the entire inside portion of the slow cooker AND also the wings. (Spraying the wings before you grill, bake, or cook chicken keeps the flavor and makes them super juicy. TRUST ME.)Take the wings and add them into the mixing bowl with your spices and toss to get a good even coat over the wings.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8558, 1295, 'Place in the slow cooker on low for 4 hours. After 4hours, remove carefully and place on a prepared cookie sheet.', 3, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8559, 1295, 'Place in the oven under broiler setting for 4-6 minutes, allowing the wings to get a little crisp.', 4, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8560, 1295, 'Serve immediately with a little blue cheese dressing and celery.', 5, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8561, 1296, 'Rinse the beans in a colander. Pick out any bad beans.', 1, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8562, 1296, 'Combine all the ingredients in the crockpot.', 2, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8563, 1296, 'Remove any floating beans. Cover, and cook on HIGH for 4 hours and on LOW for 2 hours.Uncover, and remove extra liquid. Leave enough liquid to reach the desired consistency when the beans are mashed. (We like our beans somewhere between the very-liquidy restaurant style beans, and the canned version of refried beans.)Mash beans with a potato masher to desired consistency.', 3, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8564, 1296, 'Serve warm. Store in air-tight containers in the refrigerator and use within 2 weeks, or freeze in ziplock bags for later use.', 4, '2023-04-26 07:14:35', '2023-04-26 07:14:35'),
(8565, 1297, 'Cut the tomatoes in half as straight across the diameter as you can.', 1, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8566, 1297, 'Place all of the tomatoes, cut side down on the cutting board. Insert the toothpick through one half of a tomato and slide it up the toothpick. Skewer a mozzarella ball and slide it up the toothpick until it is touching the tomato.', 2, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8567, 1297, 'Place one small basil leaf (or half of a large leaf) onto the skewer. Then with the tomato resting on the cutting board, cut side down, insert the toothpick as straight as possible into the tomato so that the tomato makes a base for the remainder of the toothpick.', 3, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8568, 1297, 'Sprinkle with salt and pepper.', 4, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8569, 1297, 'Drizzle with balsamic vinegar.', 5, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8570, 1297, 'Serve cold.', 6, '2023-04-26 08:24:22', '2023-04-26 08:24:22'),
(8571, 1298, 'Prepare all vegetables. Leeks need extra attention when cleaning as they contain a lot of sand. To properly clean a leek remove the roots and the dark green ends, so just the white and light green part remains. Slice the leek length wise, halfway through, so all of its layers are visible. Rinse under cold water carefully pulling back layers to remove the sand. Shake off excess water and slice into thin discs.In a large pot or dutch oven, melt butter over medium high heat. Saut leeks, onions and garlic for roughly 3-5 minutes until tender. Do not brown the leeks as it will give your soup a burnt flavour.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:27', '2023-04-28 07:37:27'),
(8572, 1298, 'Add potatoes, carrots, and celery. Cook for an additional 5 minutes stirring frequently.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:27', '2023-04-28 07:37:27'),
(8573, 1298, 'Sprinkle with parsley, thyme, red pepper flakes, and rosemary, stir to combine.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:27', '2023-04-28 07:37:27'),
(8574, 1298, 'Pour in chicken broth and season with Worcestershire sauce.Bring soup to a boil and cook for about 5 minutes. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25-35 minutes.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:27', '2023-04-28 07:37:27'),
(8575, 1298, 'Remove from heat.Using a blender, puree soup in batches until smooth. Salt and pepper to taste.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:27', '2023-04-28 07:37:27'),
(8576, 1299, 'Make the crust: Pulse the flour, sugar and salt in a food processor.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8577, 1299, 'Add 1 stick butter and pulse until combined.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8578, 1299, 'Add the remaining 2 sticks butter and pulse three times, or until the mixture resembles coarse meal.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8579, 1300, 'Heat oven to 350 degrees and butter a 2-quart gratin dish. Wash the leeks and slice thinly crosswise.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8580, 1300, 'Using a mandoline (or knife), slice the potatoes into 1/8-inch thick rounds. Toss with 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8581, 1300, 'Layer the rounds in the gratin dish.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8582, 1300, 'Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8583, 1300, 'Add leeks, remaining salt and pepper, and thyme. Cook, stirring, until leeks are tender and golden, about 5 minutes. Discard thyme and place the leeks over the potatoes.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8584, 1300, 'Add cream, garlic and bay leaf to the skillet, scraping up browned bits of leeks from the bottom of the pan. Simmer gently for 5 minutes. Stir in nutmeg.', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8585, 1300, 'Pour the cream over the leeks and potatoes and top with the Gruyre. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes, uncover and bake until the cheese is bubbling and golden, 15 to 20 minutes longer.', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8586, 1300, 'Let cool slightly before serving.', 8, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8587, 1301, 'Place cut potatoes in a large saucepan, with enough salted cold water to cover the potatoes by 1/2 inch.Bring to a simmer and cook for 20 to 25 minutes until they are tender but not falling apart.While the potatoes are cooking, in a small saucepan heat the milk, butter, chopped garlic and Chavrie Goat Cheese over moderately low heat, stirring, until the butter and goat cheese are just melted and smooth. Keep the mixture warm.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8588, 1301, 'Drain the potatoes well and while still warm mix. with an electric mixer for 2 minutes. fold in the Chavrie mixture, the scallion, and salt and pepper to taste, and mix until the potatoes are fluffy and smooth 1-2 minutes', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8589, 1301, 'Transfer the mixture to a 9 inch baking dish. (The potatoes may be prepared up to this point 2 days in advance and kept covered and chilled).', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8590, 1301, 'Bake in a 350 degree oven until golden brown 20-25 minutes', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8591, 1302, 'Boil the potatoes in a saucepan until soft.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8592, 1302, 'Drain, then add the sour cream, milk and butter and mash until smooth.In a mixing bowl, stir the flours,yeast, sugar and salt together.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8593, 1302, 'Add half of the eggwash, potatoes mixture then, using a dough hook, mix everything to form a dough.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8594, 1302, 'Add the scallion and continue to knead for about 15 minutes until the dough is smooth and elastic.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8595, 1302, 'Add a little oil to another bowl and add in the dough. Turn over a few times to very lightly coat all sides of the dough.Cover the dough with plastic wrap and allow to rest till double in bulk, about 1 hour. After the dough has risen, pour out onto a clean flat surface. Punch down the dough to release some of the air. Devide the dough into 8 pieces and shape each into a round form.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8596, 1302, 'Place the rounds onto a parchment lined cookie sheet. Cover with plastic warp and allow to rise for another 40-50 minutes.', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8597, 1302, 'Brush the rolls with the remaining eggwash and bake into a preheated 350F oven for 22-25 minutes.', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8598, 1302, 'Remove and cool on a wire rack before served.', 8, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8599, 1303, 'Boil potatoes in salted water until fairly soft but not mushy, approximately 10-15 minutes.While potatoes boil, roast tomatoes and red onion in 400 degree oven until onions soften and tomatoes begin to burst, approximately 20-25 minutes.When potatoes are ready, drain in a colander and place in a large bowl. Drop green beans into potato water and cook until bright green and firm, approximately 5 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8600, 1303, 'Drain and run under cold water to stop the cooking process.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8601, 1303, 'Add to the bowl with potatoes.Once tomatoes and onions are done, stir into green beans and potatoes.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8602, 1303, 'Add garlic and herbs.Just before serving, douse with olive oil and salt to taste.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:28', '2023-04-28 07:37:28'),
(8603, 1304, 'In a saucepan, fry  garlic in olive oil until tender.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8604, 1304, 'Add potatoes, oregano and a pinch of salt.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8605, 1304, 'Cover with water (300 ml-400ml) and cook for 30 minutes or until potatoes are soft OR', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8606, 1304, 'To speed up cooking, cook the potatoes, with some water, in a microwave oven for 15 minutes on MAX.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8607, 1304, 'Puree potatoes, peppers or pepper sauce and  4 olives in a blender.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8608, 1304, 'Add water if too thick, season with pepper and salt.', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8609, 1304, 'Serve warm or hot, decorated with remaining olives.', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8610, 1305, 'Heat oven to 425F', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8611, 1305, 'Wash beets, trim ends (do not peel) and wrap in foil', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8612, 1305, 'Place on baking dish and roast for about 90 minutes', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8613, 1305, 'Open, cool slightly and easily peel the skin off', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8614, 1305, 'For the soup: Slice leeks', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8615, 1305, 'Heat oil in a heavy bottomed pot and saut for about 10 minutes then add your seasonings (salt, pepper and Scarborough Fair)', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8616, 1305, 'Add the diced potatoes, chervil, and chicken stock', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8617, 1305, 'Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender', 8, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8618, 1305, 'When soup is done, remove a few ladles of the potato chunks into a bowl', 9, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8619, 1305, 'Pure remaining soup with an immersion blender', 10, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8620, 1305, 'If you want a thicker soup, return to heat and use a cornstarch/water mixture to thicken', 11, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8621, 1305, 'Return potato chunks to the pot', 12, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8622, 1305, 'Ladle soup into a bowl and garnish with some of the diced roasted beets.', 13, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8623, 1305, 'Enjoy.', 14, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8624, 1306, 'In a large pan, heat 4 Tbsp butter until it bubbles. ', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8625, 1306, 'Then add the chopped leeks. Season with 1/2 tsp kosher salt and 1/2 tsp pepper. Stir occasionally for about 10 minutes until the leeks get really soft and the edges begin to brown. ', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8626, 1306, 'Add garlic and stir for another couple of minutes. Taste before the next step. ', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8627, 1306, 'Add 5 c liquid (I use 50% chicken stock and 50% water) and the herbs. Taste and see if you like the balance so far. Some stocks are saltier than others. ', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8628, 1306, 'Crank up the heat to bring it to a quick boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8629, 1306, 'Add 1 lb of thinly sliced Yukon gold potatoes and let it simmer with the lid on for about 40 minutes. Stir occasionally.', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8630, 1306, 'The soup is done when the potatoes are very tender and starting to fall apart. We might still have to add some more salt and pepper. Potatoes soak up some salt. Taste again. Season with salt until you achieve the desired yumminess. If you like, add a pinch of cayenne pepper, which really makes it pop. ', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8631, 1306, 'Serve in a bowl, add a splash of heavy cream (if desired), and top with some fresh flat-leaf Italian parsley.', 8, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8632, 1306, 'If you prefer a creamy consistency, use an immersion blender and blend everything together before serving. ', 9, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8633, 1307, 'Heat oil and butter in a Dutch oven or large pan over medium heat.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8634, 1307, 'Add onions and cook for 5 minutes to soften.', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8635, 1307, 'Add garlic and cook another few minutes. Then add vegetable broth, potatoes, bay leaves, and thyme. Bring to a boil and cover. Cook for 20 minutes until vegetables are very tender.', 3, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8636, 1307, 'When potatoes are tender add sun-dried tomatoes. Cook for another 5 minutes, remove bay leaves and add buttermilk.', 4, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8637, 1307, 'Remove from heat and using an immersion blender, blend being sure to leave small chunks of potatoes.', 5, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8638, 1307, 'Add turkey ham and return to the burner for a few minutes to heat the ham through.', 6, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8639, 1307, 'Serve with sour cream and parsley.', 7, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8640, 1308, 'Wash six medium sized potatoes, and cook in boiling salted water until soft. Cool, remove skins, and cut in very thin slices. Cover bottom of baking-dish with potatoes, season with salt and pepper, sprinkle with finely chopped celery, then with finely chopped parsley.', 1, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8641, 1308, 'Mix two tablespoons each tarragon and cider vinegar and four tablespoons olive oil, and add one slice lemon cut one third inch thick. Bring to boiling-point, pour over potatoes, cover, and let stand in oven until thoroughly', 2, '2023-04-28 07:37:29', '2023-04-28 07:37:29'),
(8642, 1309, 'Firstly, get your popsicle molds out and ready to be used!', 1, '2023-04-28 09:01:57', '2023-04-28 09:01:57'),
(8643, 1309, 'Put all of the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. This could take a few minutes depending on your blender.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:01:57', '2023-04-28 09:01:57'),
(8644, 1309, 'Pour mixture into popsicle molds and freeze it overnight.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:01:57', '2023-04-28 09:01:57'),
(8645, 1309, 'The next day, run the popsicles under hot water for a few seconds to easily take the popsicle out of the mold.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:01:57', '2023-04-28 09:01:57'),
(8646, 1309, 'Eat and enjoy!', 5, '2023-04-28 09:01:57', '2023-04-28 09:01:57'),
(8647, 1310, 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8648, 1310, 'Cut fruit into 1 pieces and place in a medium mixing bowl.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8649, 1310, 'Add citrus juices, sugar, and cinnamon.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8650, 1310, 'Mix well and set aside.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8651, 1310, 'Add butter to baking pan and place in oven until completely melted. Meanwhile, make the batter: using a wire whisk, mix all dry ingredients together until well blended. Slowly beat in half and half until a smooth batter forms.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8652, 1310, 'Pour batter over melted butter. Using a slotted spoon, add peach mixture on top of the batter and bake for 55 minutes, or until top of cobbler is golden brown.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8653, 1310, 'Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or fresh whipped cream.', 7, '2023-04-28 09:02:10', '2023-04-28 09:02:10'),
(8654, 1311, 'Cut the nectarine in half and remove the pit.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8655, 1311, 'Cut into small or medium-sized pieces and place in a medium-sized bowl. Try to make all the other items the same size. If you want a chunky style salsa, use larger pieces. If you want the salsa to be more refined, you can cut things pretty small.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8656, 1311, 'Cut up the mango, holding it over the bowl to capture the juice.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8657, 1311, 'Juice the lime and add to the bowl.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8658, 1311, 'Halve the jalapeno and the red pepper, removing the ribs, stem, and seeds.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8659, 1311, 'Cut up the avocado and add the salt and pepper.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8660, 1311, 'Mix well, making sure the avocado gets coated with juice. You can serve at once or place in the refrigerator for several hours for the flavors to meld.', 7, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8661, 1312, 'Blend everything together in a blender until smooth.Refrigerate over night.Churn in your ice cream maker as according to the manufacturer\'s instruction.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8662, 1313, 'Using a fork, hand-mix everything together in a big bowl and pour into your ice cream maker. Follow your maker\'s instructions.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8663, 1313, 'If you DON\'T have a ice cream maker. Simply pour the mixture into a plastic bowl and put in freezer. When frozen... take it out, let it soften a little (not too much!) and scoop it into your blender. Blend till creamy (not too long!).', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:11', '2023-04-28 09:02:11'),
(8664, 1314, 'Peel and slice the mango lengthwise, about 1/4-inch thick.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:12', '2023-04-28 09:02:12'),
(8665, 1314, 'Lay the slices on the plate.Using an electric mixer, whip the cream, vanilla and stevia until stiff peaks form.In a 9x13 rectangular dish, layer graham crackers on the bottom of the dish; spread some whipped cream over the crackers, then arrange some mango slices over the cream. Repeat the process, ending with whipped cream. Top with finely crushed graham crackers; cover with a plastic wrap and refrigerate for 6-8 hours or even better if chilled overnight.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:12', '2023-04-28 09:02:12'),
(8666, 1315, 'Mix all the ingredients together in a medium-sized bowl then serve.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:12', '2023-04-28 09:02:12'),
(8667, 1316, 'Prepare the banana the night before. Peel, slice, and place on a small parchment lined tray. Pop into the freezer.The same can be done with the mango, but I used frozen mango pieces for convenience.Toss all of the ingredients into a blender and blend until smooth, adding more water if necessary. If you like, add some freshly squeezed orange juice for a citrusy flavour.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:13', '2023-04-28 09:02:13'),
(8668, 1316, 'Serve cold.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:13', '2023-04-28 09:02:13'),
(8669, 1317, 'Smoothie 1: blueberries, strawberries, pomegranate juice Smoothie 2: mangos, orange juice', 1, '2023-04-28 09:02:13', '2023-04-28 09:02:13');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(8670, 1317, 'If you have an immersion blender, place the ingredients for each smoothie into its own quart-sized mason jar or a really large cup. Blend one smoothie, rinse off the blender, then blend the other.If you\'re using a blender, blend smoothies one at a time, rinsing the blender between uses.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:02:13', '2023-04-28 09:02:13'),
(8671, 1317, 'Pour the smoothies together into serving cups, creating a swirled effect.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:02:13', '2023-04-28 09:02:13'),
(8672, 1318, 'find instructions on swasthis recipes', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:15', '2023-04-28 09:03:15'),
(8673, 1319, 'Preheat the oven to 350F. Line a 9x13 pan with foil.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8674, 1319, 'In a small bowl. Sift together the flour and cocoa powder.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8675, 1319, 'Whisk in the sea salt and set aside.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8676, 1319, 'In a medium saucepan. Melt the butter and unsweetened chopped chocolate until all the chocolate is melted and the mixture is smooth.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8677, 1319, 'Stir in the sugar and vanilla.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8678, 1319, 'Remove from heat. It will look \'grainy\' because of the sugar but don\'t worry.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8679, 1319, 'Whisk/stir in the eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition. You should now have a smooth, satin-like mixture.', 7, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8680, 1319, 'Add the flour/cocoa and stir until uniform.', 8, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8681, 1319, 'Stir in the Oreos.', 9, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8682, 1319, 'Pour into prepared pan.', 10, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8683, 1319, 'Crush some extra cookies over the top.', 11, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8684, 1319, 'Bake for about 35 minutes. A tester should be free of any batter but have a few moist crumbs.', 12, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8685, 1320, 'Preheat oven to 175 C (350 F)In a bowl, using an electric whisk, whisk together the egg and the sugar until smooth and there\'s no lumps left.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8686, 1320, 'Add milk, butter, vanilla and peppermint to the mixture and mix until combined.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8687, 1320, 'Add the dry ingredients (flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt) and mix with the mixture until well combined and there\'s no pockets of flour or cocoa. Stir in sour cream.Either grease a cupcake tin or line it with cupcake cases. If you want to be particular, add about 1/4 of cup of mixture to each cupcake case.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8688, 1320, 'Bake your cupcakes for 15-18 mins and then allow them to sit in the tin for about 30 mins until cool and then place them on a wire rack.Set-up a double boiler (heat-resistant glass bowl on top of a pot of simmering water) and add to that the egg whites, sugar and salt.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8689, 1320, 'Whisk occasionally until either the mixture has reached 160 F or (like me if you didn\'t have a sugar thermometer) wait until the sugar has melted.You won\'t really be able to tell when the sugar has melted but the meringue has to be HOT HOT HOT. Just about too hot to touch. Once you\'ve reached that stage, throw into an electric mixer and put it on a low setting with the whisk attachment and whisk it until the bottom of the bowl is cool to the touch (10-15 mins).Now turn it up to a higher speed and whisk the meringue till you get stiff peaks. Once you\'ve got stiff peaks, add the butter a little at a time (about 2-3tbsps) allowing it to be completely mixed in before adding anymore. It might curdle at some point, this happens, just put the mixer on a high speed and it will eventually come together.Once you\'re happy with your icing, add 2-3 tsps of peppermint, and colour it mint green. And then ice your cupcakes!', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8690, 1320, 'Drizzle with chocolate sauce and shove a whole cupcake into your mouth/face.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8691, 1321, 'In a bowl, mix the chia seeds and milk together.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8692, 1321, 'Let the chia seeds sit for about a minute or two and stir the mixture. The chia seeds will start to clump up very quickly, so use a fork to break them apart.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8693, 1321, 'Allow the chia seeds to continue soaking up the liquid for another few minutes and stir it again.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8694, 1321, 'Mix in the cocoa powder, agave, and peppermint extract and stir.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8695, 1321, 'Once the chia and milk mixture have turned into the consistency of pudding, put the mixture into a jar or airtight container and refrigerate for one to two hours. I refrigerated mine overnight.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8696, 1321, 'Top the pudding with your favorite fruits, nuts, or nut butter in the morning!', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:16', '2023-04-28 09:03:16'),
(8697, 1322, 'Pour the water, sugar and lemon zest into a pot over medium high heat until the sugar has completely dissolved, stirring occasionally.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8698, 1322, 'Remove from heat, stir in the mint and set aside.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8699, 1322, 'As the simple syrup steeps, whisk together the lemon juice, limoncello and salt.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8700, 1322, 'Pour into the minted simple syrup and allow to cool completely. Chill for at least 3 hours, but preferably overnight.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8701, 1322, 'Once the liquid has chilled, pour it into the frozen base of your ice cream maker, cover with the lid and churn for 20-30 minutes or until the mixture thickens.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8702, 1322, 'Put the base into the freezer for another hour or two to harden as desired.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8703, 1323, 'Toast cumin in a dry small heavy skillet over medium heat, shaking skillet frequently, until fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8704, 1323, 'Transfer 1 1/2 teaspoons to a blender with mint, yogurt, kosher salt, and water.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8705, 1323, 'Blend until pale green with flecks of mint and cumin.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8706, 1323, 'Serve lassi over ice and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon cumin seeds.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:17', '2023-04-28 09:03:17'),
(8707, 1324, 'In a tall glass, add the mint and simple syrup. With the handle of a spoon, crush and mash the leaves to extract the flavors. Fill the glass with the crushed ice and pour in the bourbon. Using a tea spoon, jiggle the contents to mix and chill.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:18', '2023-04-28 09:03:18'),
(8708, 1324, 'Strain into a julep cup filled with crushed ice.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:18', '2023-04-28 09:03:18'),
(8709, 1324, 'Garnish with fresh mint sprigs.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:18', '2023-04-28 09:03:18'),
(8710, 1325, 'Combine the flax, applesauce and almond milk together in a small bowl. Set aside to allow to thicken. In a food processor, combine the blueberries, pear, black beans and oil. Pulse until the mixture become very smooth. Next, add the extracts and process until fully combined.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8711, 1325, 'Remove the contents from processor into a medium sized mixing bowl.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8712, 1325, 'Add the coconut sugar, cocoa, baking powder, soda, and salt and mix.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8713, 1325, 'Add the flour with the chocolate chips and mix until just combined.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8714, 1325, 'Pour the batter into your prepared dish and bake at 350 for 44-45 minutes.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8715, 1325, 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool for at least 50 minutes. If you would like, place the brownies in the fridge for 20 or 30 minutes to speed up cooling time. While the brownies cool, start on your mint filling.In a small bowl, combine the soft avocado with full fat coconut milk or heavy cream. Beat on high for about 5 minutes until the mixture is fluffy and smooth.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8716, 1325, 'Add the powdered xylitol and mix well.', 7, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8717, 1325, 'Add peppermint extract and coloring if desired, and beat until all incorporated. Once the mixture is perfectly fluffy and creamy, add the flour and mix until just combined. The mixture should be thick and smooth but still easy to spread.', 8, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8718, 1325, 'Spread the mixture evenly over the cooled brownies and place in the fridge for 10 minutes, until the mint filling has firmed.Next, melt the chocolate.', 9, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8719, 1325, 'Add the oil to the melted chocolate and stir to combine.', 10, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8720, 1325, 'Remove the brownies from the fridge and pour the melted chocolate over the brownies, gently and quickly spread the chocolate evenly over the brownies. The mint filling should be cold so the warm chocolate doesnt melt the mint filling, but the chocolate will cool quickly once it touches the cold mint. Make sure to work quickly so the chocolate layer will be even. Return the brownies to the fridge to cool for another 5 minutes until the chocolate is set.', 11, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8721, 1325, 'Cut the brownies after the 5 minutes with a sharp knife.', 12, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8722, 1325, 'Serve brownies chilled or at room temperature. Store any left overs in an airtight container in the refrigerator.NOTE: Once the chocolate layer has firmed, be sure to cut all the brownies immediately with a sharp knife. I cut some of the brownies when they were really, really cold, and they didnt cut clean and pretty.*For those who are not concerned with gluten content, wheat or white flour would work okay as well. For wheat, decrease the amount by 1 tablespoon. For the filling, be sure to use a white color flour to keep the mint filling a bright pretty green color.**You can use any kind of chocolate you like, but dark chocolate gives a wonderful flavor to the peppermint and sugar free dark chocolate is the easiest to find.', 13, '2023-04-28 09:03:19', '2023-04-28 09:03:19'),
(8723, 1326, 'Wash and peel the kiwis.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:20', '2023-04-28 09:03:20'),
(8724, 1326, 'Cut them into thin slices. Wash the mint sprigs.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:20', '2023-04-28 09:03:20'),
(8725, 1326, 'Place kiwi slices and mint in a large jar/bottle.Fill the jar/bottle with water and cover.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:20', '2023-04-28 09:03:20'),
(8726, 1326, 'Place in the fridge and chill for at least 2 hours, for best results overnight.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:20', '2023-04-28 09:03:20'),
(8727, 1327, 'Whip together the spread, thinly slice the cucumbers. You can do thick crunchy slices, or thin silky slices - your choice. Gather your fresh herbs, rinse and pat dry.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8728, 1327, 'Spread a very thin layer of spread on all inside surfaces of bread.', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8729, 1327, 'Layer cucumber on top of the spread. Next, add a layer of mint, dill. You can add both herbs to each sandwich or do half dill and half mint. Grind fresh black pepper inside sandwiches before slicing.', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8730, 1327, 'Close sandwich and slice into quarter cubes or triangles.', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8731, 1327, 'Plate and serve.', 5, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8732, 1327, 'Optional: add a thin layer of spicy sun dried tomato spread or a dash of red pepper flakes for an extra spicy kick of flavor. Another pretty addition would be edible flowers - add inside the sandwiches or as an edible garnish to the serving patter.', 6, '2023-04-28 09:03:21', '2023-04-28 09:03:21'),
(8733, 1328, 'Scrub and slice the cucumber.Wash the mint.Scrub and slice the lime.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
(8734, 1328, 'Place the cucumber slices, mint, and lime slices in a large pitcher or bottle. Fill with water. Cover and refrigerate for 1-8 hours (the longer you infuse the water, the stronger the flavor.)', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
(8735, 1329, 'Allow to cool for 5 minutes, then transfer to the refrigerator for 90 minutes.', 1, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
(8736, 1329, 'Remove and break into pieces to serve.How easy is that? Not to mention, it really is super delicious candy bark! Are you making anything fun for St. Patricks Day? If not, this would be a quick and easy treat to share with everyone.I hope you enjoyed this quick recipe for Chocolate Mint Marble Bark with Almonds, and I will be back soon with another treat to share!JOIN 500,000 SUBSCRIBERS!Join over 500,000 others who follow Pink', 2, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
(8737, 1329, 'When on Social Media, the Pink', 3, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
(8738, 1329, 'When blog, and email. Sign up to receive exclusive bonuses like this FREE Simple Fit Dinners Ebook.Don\'t wait! You won\'t want to miss a thing.Success! Now check your email to confirm your subscription and download your FREE ebook.There was an error submitting your subscription. Please try again.First Name', 4, '2023-04-28 09:03:22', '2023-04-28 09:03:22'),
