(9387, 1440, 'Pat the chickpeas dry with a paper towel and throw them into a food processor along with the garlic.', 1, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9388, 1440, 'Puree until smooth.', 2, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9389, 1440, 'Using your clean hands incorporate tahini, sriracha, parsley and onion into the chickpea mixture.', 3, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9390, 1440, 'Form mixture into four patties and set aside.', 4, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9391, 1440, 'Heat peanut oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 5, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9392, 1440, 'Once the oil begins to shimmer add the patties and cook for three minutes per side or until golden brown.', 6, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9393, 1440, 'Remove from and place in a hamburger bun.', 7, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9394, 1440, 'Top each burger with 2 slices of tomato, 2 slices of cucumber and a dollop of tzatziki.', 8, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9395, 1440, 'Serve immediately.', 9, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9396, 1441, 'Irish Mustard Sauce: 1 tbsp cornstarch, 2 tsp sugar, 1 tsp dry mustard, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 cup water, 1 tbsp butter, 1/4 cup vinegar, 1 tsp horseradish, 2 egg yolks, beaten. Put all ingredients in a sauce pan over medium heat. Continue whisking until smooth and thickened to consistency of pudding.', 1, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9397, 1441, 'Gorgonzola Butter-Wash: In a microwave safe bowl, add remaining tablespoon of Gorgonzola crumbles and 2 tablespoons of butter and melt.', 2, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9398, 1441, 'Whisk together to create a Gorgonzola butter-wash.', 3, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9399, 1441, 'Brush Gorgonzola butter-wash on the inside of the top & bottom buns and toast on the upper or outer edges of grill. Once rolls are lightly toasted, remove.', 4, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9400, 1442, 'Save 2 tbsp butter and keep cold in refrigerator.In small saucepan, melt remaining butter; keep warm.In a stainless steel bowl, whisk egg yolks until thickened and pale.', 1, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9401, 1442, 'Whisk in water and lemon juice.', 2, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9402, 1442, 'Add 1 tbsp of the cold butter.This will make your arm burn, and if it doesn\'t you are in wayyyy better shape than me - congratulations', 3, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9403, 1442, 'Set the bowl over a pot with about 2 inches of barely simmering water; whisk until bottom of pan can be seen between whisks and wires of whisk become lightly coated, 1 to 2 minutes. Oh yay, arm burn again!', 4, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9404, 1443, 'Heat the grill to high. Divide the ground beef into 4 portions. Salt and pepper and press into patties.', 1, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9405, 1443, 'Layer each patty with a slice of pancetta on top and bottom. Press the pancetta into the patty.', 2, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9406, 1443, 'Cut the onion and mozzarella into rounds.', 3, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9407, 1443, 'Melt the butter and mix it with the tomato paste and anchovy paste.', 4, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9408, 1443, 'Cut the ciabatta buns and brush the insides with tomato-butter.', 5, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9409, 1443, 'CAREFULLY brush the grill with oil or use non-stick grill spray. Grill the patties and onions at the same time. Grill the patties for 3-5 minutes per side and the onions for 1-2 minutes per side.', 6, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9410, 1443, 'Once you flip the burgers, lay the onion rounds over the top of each patty, followed by the mozzarella slices. The cheese will melt while the burgers finish cooking.', 7, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9411, 1443, 'Place the buns on the open grill and toast for 1 minute.', 8, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9412, 1443, 'Once the buns are toasted, slather them with pesto.', 9, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9413, 1443, 'Layer arugula leaves, tomato slices and a patty on each bun. Top and serve!', 10, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9414, 1443, 'Serves 4.', 11, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9415, 1444, 'Combine everything but onion, salsa, and buns in a large bowl, shape into four patties.', 1, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9416, 1444, 'Heat a skillet sprayed with non-stick over medium-high heat. Cook burgers until done (160F internal temperature) about 5 minutes a side.Top with cheese (if desired), one onion slice and two tablespoons salsa.', 2, '2023-05-03 06:35:40', '2023-05-03 06:35:40'),
(9417, 1445, 'Burger', 1, '2023-05-03 06:39:43', '2023-05-03 06:39:43'),
(9418, 1446, 'Cook potato in microwave. Slice and cut into thin strips.In a small saut pan heat butter over medium heat.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:00:25', '2023-05-03 08:00:25'),
(9419, 1446, 'Add potato to pan and lightly brown potato, season with salt and pepper.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:00:25', '2023-05-03 08:00:25'),
(9420, 1446, 'Add eggs to potato. Stir to scramble and combine.Wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:00:25', '2023-05-03 08:00:25'),
(9421, 1446, 'Heat in microwave for about 45 seconds.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:00:25', '2023-05-03 08:00:25'),
(9422, 1446, 'Place equal amounts in each tortilla and top with shredded cheese.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:00:25', '2023-05-03 08:00:25'),
(9423, 1447, 'In a small bowl combine the cumin, chili powder, paprika, 1 minced clove of garlic and 2 tbsp of olive oil.  Slice the tofu very thin, about 1/2 inch per slice, then rub each slice with the spice mixture.  Set aside.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9424, 1447, 'Heat about 1 tbsp olive oil over medium high heat in a large pan.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9425, 1447, 'Add the tofu, a few slices at a time, watching carefully.  Flip after about 1-2 minutes.  Cook until done  I let mine cook about 2-3 minutes per side.   Half each piece, wrap with bacon, then set aside and cover with aluminum foil.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9426, 1447, 'Do NOT wash the pan out  now put it back on the stove, reduce heat to medium and add the remaining minced garlic clove, 1 tbsp olive oil and diced jalapeno.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9427, 1447, 'Saute until the peppers are almost getting a little bit brown and everything is fragrant.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9428, 1447, 'Add the cream cheese, 1/2 cup cheese and chicken broth.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9429, 1447, 'Whisk and bring to a slight boil; reducing the heat if you have to, preventing it from scorching. Once its combined and a sauce consistency, salt and pepper to your taste and pour into a separate bowl; cover.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9430, 1447, 'Bring the heat back up to medium-high, and add another tablespoon of olive oil to the pan.  When hot add one tortilla at a time, turning after about 15-20 seconds to the other side.  Your end result will be tortillas slightly brown around the edges and a little bubbly in the middle.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9431, 1447, 'Set aside and cover.', 9, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9432, 1447, 'To serve, stuff a tortilla with bacon-wrapped tofu, and drizzle the jalapeno creme on top and some Monterey jack.', 10, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9433, 1448, 'Heat the oil in a large non-stick frying pan over medium-high heat.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9434, 1448, 'Add onion and mushrooms; cook and stir for 3-4 minutes or until lightly browned.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9435, 1448, 'Add carrot, zucchini, taco seasoning mix and water, cook and stir to mix well. Lower heat to medium, cover and cook about 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Uncover and bring to boil until juices evaporate. To serve, place about  cup (50 mL) filling in each taco shell and top with lettuce and garnish if desired with tomato.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9436, 1448, 'Serve with guacamole if desired.Makes 12 tacos', 4, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9437, 1448, 'Tips: To save time, buy pre-sliced mushrooms and grate carrot and zucchini in food processor.  To warm taco shells separate and place the shells onto a baking tray and heat in 350F (18', 5, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9438, 1448, 'for 10 minutes or until hot.Variation: Taco Salad: Reduce oil to 1 tbsp (15 mL); add  lb (250 g) lean ground beef with onion and cook, stirring often until beef is browned; then add mushrooms, carrot and zucchini and continue as directed above.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9439, 1448, 'Serve hot mixture over salad greens; top with sour cream and chopped green onions.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9440, 1448, 'Garnish plate with tomato wedges and taco chips.For more delicious recipe ideas visit Mushrooms Canada at www.mushrooms.ca.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:00:26', '2023-05-03 08:00:26'),
(9441, 1449, 'Pat the chickpeas dry with a paper towel and throw them into a food processor along with the garlic.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9442, 1449, 'Puree until smooth.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9443, 1449, 'Using your clean hands incorporate tahini, sriracha, parsley and onion into the chickpea mixture.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9444, 1449, 'Form mixture into four patties and set aside.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9445, 1449, 'Heat peanut oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9446, 1449, 'Once the oil begins to shimmer add the patties and cook for three minutes per side or until golden brown.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9447, 1449, 'Remove from and place in a hamburger bun.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9448, 1449, 'Top each burger with 2 slices of tomato, 2 slices of cucumber and a dollop of tzatziki.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9449, 1449, 'Serve immediately.', 9, '2023-05-03 08:02:14', '2023-05-03 08:02:14'),
(9450, 1450, 'Irish Mustard Sauce: 1 tbsp cornstarch, 2 tsp sugar, 1 tsp dry mustard, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 cup water, 1 tbsp butter, 1/4 cup vinegar, 1 tsp horseradish, 2 egg yolks, beaten. Put all ingredients in a sauce pan over medium heat. Continue whisking until smooth and thickened to consistency of pudding.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9451, 1450, 'Gorgonzola Butter-Wash: In a microwave safe bowl, add remaining tablespoon of Gorgonzola crumbles and 2 tablespoons of butter and melt.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9452, 1450, 'Whisk together to create a Gorgonzola butter-wash.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16');
INSERT INTO `recipe_steps` (`id`, `recipe_id`, `description`, `order_step`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(9453, 1450, 'Brush Gorgonzola butter-wash on the inside of the top & bottom buns and toast on the upper or outer edges of grill. Once rolls are lightly toasted, remove.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9454, 1451, 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees.In a medium bowl add 2 T of mustard and a generous pinch of salt to the ground beef. Using your hands, mix gently until everything is thoroughly combined.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9455, 1451, 'Roll meat into very small balls, roughly 1 1/2 inches across and set on a rimmed cookie sheet. (I got 16 out of my batch.) Press each ball down gently to slightly flatten .', 2, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9456, 1451, 'Bake for 10 minutes, remove and lay a small piece of cheese over each burger. Return to oven for 1-2 more minutes until cheese is melted and burgers are cooked through.While the burgers are cooking, spread mustard on buns (if you like), and cut into 1-inch pieces. Prepare remaining ingredients and have everything ready when the burgers come out of the oven.Assemble burgers on toothpicks by stabbing some bread (mustard side down), then lettuce, then tomato, then a burger, then the other piece of bread (mustard side up). When you put them on a serving dish, press everything down a bit -- that will help them stand up.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9457, 1452, 'Save 2 tbsp butter and keep cold in refrigerator.In small saucepan, melt remaining butter; keep warm.In a stainless steel bowl, whisk egg yolks until thickened and pale.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9458, 1452, 'Whisk in water and lemon juice.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9459, 1452, 'Add 1 tbsp of the cold butter.This will make your arm burn, and if it doesn\'t you are in wayyyy better shape than me - congratulations', 3, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9460, 1452, 'Set the bowl over a pot with about 2 inches of barely simmering water; whisk until bottom of pan can be seen between whisks and wires of whisk become lightly coated, 1 to 2 minutes. Oh yay, arm burn again!', 4, '2023-05-03 08:02:16', '2023-05-03 08:02:16'),
(9461, 1453, 'Heat the grill to high. Divide the ground beef into 4 portions. Salt and pepper and press into patties.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9462, 1453, 'Layer each patty with a slice of pancetta on top and bottom. Press the pancetta into the patty.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9463, 1453, 'Cut the onion and mozzarella into rounds.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9464, 1453, 'Melt the butter and mix it with the tomato paste and anchovy paste.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9465, 1453, 'Cut the ciabatta buns and brush the insides with tomato-butter.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9466, 1453, 'CAREFULLY brush the grill with oil or use non-stick grill spray. Grill the patties and onions at the same time. Grill the patties for 3-5 minutes per side and the onions for 1-2 minutes per side.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9467, 1453, 'Once you flip the burgers, lay the onion rounds over the top of each patty, followed by the mozzarella slices. The cheese will melt while the burgers finish cooking.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9468, 1453, 'Place the buns on the open grill and toast for 1 minute.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9469, 1453, 'Once the buns are toasted, slather them with pesto.', 9, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9470, 1453, 'Layer arugula leaves, tomato slices and a patty on each bun. Top and serve!', 10, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9471, 1453, 'Serves 4.', 11, '2023-05-03 08:02:17', '2023-05-03 08:02:17'),
(9472, 1454, 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high. When hot, add the pancetta and shallots.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9473, 1454, 'Saute for 1-2 minutes, then add the garlic and rosemary.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9474, 1454, 'Saute another 1-2 minutes.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9475, 1454, 'Add the clams, wine, red pepper, and lemon zest to the skillet. Salt and pepper; then cover. Drop the pappardelle in the boiling water.Cook the clams for 7-8 minutes, until they are mostly open. Cook the pasta for 6-8 minutes until just al dente.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9476, 1454, 'Add the cream to the clam sauce and stir. Then strain the pasta and add it straight to the clam sauce. Make sure to reserve a little pasta water. Stir the pasta and cook another 1-2 minutes.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9477, 1454, 'Add the Parmesan cheese and toss. If the sauce is thicker than desired add a little pasta water. Throw out any clams that didnt open.Plate and garnish with parsley.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9478, 1454, 'Serve immediately.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9479, 1454, 'Serves 4.You could lighten this dish by reducing or removing the heavy cream.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:03:54', '2023-05-03 08:03:54'),
(9480, 1455, 'Heat oil in heavy large pot over medium-high heat.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9481, 1455, 'Add bacon and saut until just beginning to brown (about 5-6 minutes).', 2, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9482, 1455, 'Add onion, celery, carrot, garlic, and thyme; saut 5 minutes.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9483, 1455, 'Add veal and pork; saut until brown and cooked through, breaking up meat with spatula, about 10 minutes.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9484, 1455, 'Add wine and bay leaves and simmer until liquid is slightly reduced, about 10 minutes.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9485, 1455, 'Add broth and tomato puree, then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until sauce thickens, stirring often, about 1 hour.Season with salt and pepper.Boil pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender but al dente (firm to bite), stirring often.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9486, 1455, 'Drain.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9487, 1455, 'Transfer to pot with sauce; toss.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9488, 1455, 'Serve with Parmesan.', 9, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9489, 1456, 'Cut the shell with an X where the shell bulges outward.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9490, 1456, 'Place the chestnuts in a dish and completely cover with water and soak for 20 minutes.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9491, 1456, 'Place in a baking dish and roast at 400  for 20 to 25 minutes.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9492, 1456, 'Remove from oven, peel, and chop!Bring water to a boil, season with salt, and boil the egg pasta for 6-8 min, until cooked.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9493, 1456, 'Drain and toss with a little olive oil to prevent sticking.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9494, 1456, 'Saute the sliced mushrooms in oil and a little bit of soy sauce until the aroma fills the air', 6, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9495, 1456, 'Pour in the egg mixture and scramble everything up.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9496, 1456, 'Add the chopped chestnuts and cook for another few minutes. Stir in the pasta and the remaining olive oil and mix until everything is well coated.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9497, 1456, 'Add in half of the parmesan cheese, and sprinkle in tarragon and more salt &amp; pepper to season.Turn the heat on low, add in the arugula and toss some more, making sure the arugula does not actually cook and stays crisp.Scoop onto a plate, decorate with more parmesan flakes, and fill your tummy with Christmas!', 9, '2023-05-03 08:03:55', '2023-05-03 08:03:55'),
(9498, 1457, 'Put ribs in cold water and bring to a boil', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:15', '2023-05-03 08:04:15'),
(9499, 1457, 'Add peas, browned onion and carrot and black pepper. Leave for a 1.5 hour on slow heat', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:15', '2023-05-03 08:04:15'),
(9500, 1457, 'Add bay leaves and caraway seeds. Put potato and boil more 15 min.Top with crispy fried bacon.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:15', '2023-05-03 08:04:15'),
(9501, 1458, 'Place water into a medium-sized pot. Chop up the garlic and add it to the pot, cover, and let boil for 10-15 minutes.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9502, 1458, 'Add the chickpeas and tahini, along with the salt, pepper, cumin, curry, cinnamon, and tumeric and let cook for another 20 minutes. Turn off the flame and blend (either with a hand blender or regular one). Top off with various seasonings and a drizzle of tahini for a garnish.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9503, 1459, 'In a medium saucepan, saute garlic, onions, jalapeno pepper, and celery in the olive oil for about 5 minutes.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9504, 1459, 'Add tomato pieces, chili powder, and cumin, and cook down over medium heat for about 10 minutes, stirring often.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9505, 1459, 'Add corn, basil, reserved tomato juice, and stock, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.When ready to serve, remove soup from heat and stir in the lime juice and avocado. Break several nacho chips into each bowl, ladle in the soup, then top each with a spoonful of sour cream. Toss on a few basil shreds and stick a nacho chip on top.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9506, 1459, 'Serve immediately.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9507, 1459, 'Serve hot to 6 people as complete lunch - or as a substantial first course.Comments: A wonderfully tasty, quick, low calorie, and filling soup - fit for Montezuma after a hard day at the sacrificial altar.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9508, 1460, 'In a large pan, heavy bottomed pan heat the oil on a medium high heat and add the shallot and garlic.  Fry for a minute or so allowing the shallot and garlic to soften.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9509, 1460, 'Add the chorizo and stir through giving it about 30 seconds to give off its colour and flavour.  If you are using raw chorizo you may wish to give it a little bit more time here.  Remember though, it will have enough time to cook through later.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9510, 1460, 'Add the thyme, tomato pure, paprika powder and lentils.  Stir the lentils though and then add the stock.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9511, 1460, 'Add a little bit of salt and some black pepper.  Cover your soup and allow it to simmer gently for about 20 minutes or until the lentils are cooked and softened to your taste.Check for seasoning and serve.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9512, 1461, 'It is very easy, first wash the vegetables and put it in a large pot (4 l). Usually I chop Them All, beside parsnip and celery.Fill half of the can with water THEN put it on the stove to boil.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9513, 1461, 'Add a little bit of salt.When They are ready, add the tomato juice (or puree) and the oil and Give it to boil. Taste for salt.Set aside and prepare the dumplings as Following:Beat the eggs THEN add a pinch of salt.Stir in the wheat semolina (8-10 tbsp), little by little, avoiding the lumps. The Consistency of the composition must be like a tick cream.Usually, for this soup, I boil separately Them, Because, It Happened to Me to Remain hard in the middle, so we boil Them Will separate in the can with water.Bring the water to a boil and add the dumplings with the spoon.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9514, 1461, 'Let Them When They double in size and is ready, sprinkle a little bit of cold water on Their surface. (Will this make more fluffy Them). Then add Them to the soup.Chop the parsley and put in the soup.Enjoy!', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9515, 1462, 'In a large stock pot, heat the olive oil over medium-low heat.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9516, 1462, 'Add the onion and garlic and saut until transluscent, about 4 to 5 minutes.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9517, 1462, 'Add the carrots and saut for another 2 minutes', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9518, 1462, 'Add the lentils and saut everything together about 3 minutes until lentils are glistening.While ingredients are sauting, bone the Diestel turkey thighs. Chop the meat into bite-sized pieces.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9519, 1462, 'Add the water, chicken broth, salt, pepper, bay leaf, thyme sprigs and the bones from the Diestel turkey thighs to the pot.  Bring to a boil.  Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.Check the lentils to see level of doneness  they should be soft, but should maintain their shape.  Allow soup to cook an additional 15 minutes so that the lentils can sop up more liquid.10 minutes before serving the soup, add the chopped meat. Remember it is smoked so it is already cooked all the way through  we are simply heating it up.When lentils are fully cooked and the flavors have come together, remove the thigh bone, bay leaf, thyme sprigs and serve in large heaping bowls.Grate desired amount of parmigiano reggiano on top and enjoy!', 5, '2023-05-03 08:04:16', '2023-05-03 08:04:16'),
(9520, 1463, 'Add 4 cups of water (or enough to cover the lentils plus about 2 extra inches) and the lentils to a medium-sized, deep saute pan over medium heat. Cook with the lid just slightly off the pan, for about 15-20 minutes or until the lentils are almost tender.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9521, 1463, 'Meanwhile, if you\'re using bacon (or pancetta), add it to a saute pan and cook over medium-high heat until done. When cooled, crumble the bacon into small pieces and set aside.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9522, 1463, 'In a large, deep saute pan over low-to-medium heat, add the olive oil. When hot, add the onion, carrots, garlic and celery and cook until almost soft.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9523, 1463, 'Add the tomato sauce, parsley, cream of mushroom or celery soup, 3 cups of water, and salt & pepper to taste. Bring to a boil. Once boiling, add the pasta, lower the heat and cook until the pasta is tender.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9524, 1463, 'Drain your lentils when they\'re almost soft and add them to the pasta and cook, uncovered, for another 10-15 minutes until they\'re soft.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9525, 1463, 'Add the red pepper flakes and adjust the seasonings to your taste. If you think your soup should be a bit creamier, make a roux (I used 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon flour and that was sufficient) and slowly whisk it into the lentil and pasta mixture and make sure it\'s incorporated into the soup. If you like it thinner, add a bit more water.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9526, 1463, 'Add your bacon or pancetta if your using it and mix it into the soup.', 7, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9527, 1463, 'When you\'re ready to serve, add to individual bowls and sprinkle with fresh grated Romano cheese.', 8, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9528, 1464, 'Peel and chop the beets and the onion and set aside. Chop the red pepper, mushrooms, apple, and carrots and celery.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9529, 1464, 'Add 1 cup of water to a pot, along with butter and olive oil and set to a medium heat. When the water starts to boil, add the vegetables and the apple and set to a medium heat for 20 minutes, checking on it periodically.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9530, 1464, 'Add the the rest of the water, thyme, lemon juice, and vinegar. Cover and let cook on a low flame for 30 minutes.', 3, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9531, 1464, 'Drain some of the water (about 75%) and set aside.', 4, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9532, 1464, 'Remove some chucks of beets and set aside.', 5, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9533, 1464, 'Add the remaining contents to a blender, along with the rest of the water. If you find that the soup is too thick, add more water.', 6, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9534, 1464, 'Pour into a bowl and add the beet chunks, along with', 7, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9535, 1465, 'Place pumpkin, carrots, celery and onion in large kettle.', 1, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17'),
(9536, 1465, 'Add the bay leaf and broth. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until pumpkin is tender. Put mixture in blender and return to the kettle. Stir in the remaining ingredients except the milk. Adjust the consistency with the milk.', 2, '2023-05-03 08:04:17', '2023-05-03 08:04:17');
